1751
1752void CodeGenModule::ConstructDefaultFnAttrList(StringRef Name, bool HasOptnone,
1753 bool AttrOnCallSite,
1754 llvm::AttrBuilder &FuncAttrs) {
1755 // OptimizeNoneAttr takes precedence over -Os or -Oz. No warning needed.
1756 if (!HasOptnone) {
1757 if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizeSize)
1758 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeForSize);
1759 if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizeSize == 2)
1760 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::MinSize);
1761 }
1762
1763 if (CodeGenOpts.DisableRedZone)
1764 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoRedZone);
1765 if (CodeGenOpts.IndirectTlsSegRefs)
1766 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("indirect-tls-seg-refs");
1767 if (CodeGenOpts.NoImplicitFloat)
1768 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoImplicitFloat);
1769
1770 if (AttrOnCallSite) {
1771 // Attributes that should go on the call site only.
1772 if (!CodeGenOpts.SimplifyLibCalls ||
1773 CodeGenOpts.isNoBuiltinFunc(Name.data()))
1774 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoBuiltin);
1775 if (!CodeGenOpts.TrapFuncName.empty())
1776 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("trap-func-name", CodeGenOpts.TrapFuncName);
1777 } else {
1778 // Attributes that should go on the function, but not the call site.
1779 if (!CodeGenOpts.DisableFPElim) {
1780 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-frame-pointer-elim", "false");
1781 } else if (CodeGenOpts.OmitLeafFramePointer) {
1782 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-frame-pointer-elim", "false");
1783 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-frame-pointer-elim-non-leaf");
1784 } else {
1785 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-frame-pointer-elim", "true");
1786 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-frame-pointer-elim-non-leaf");
1787 }
1788
1789 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("less-precise-fpmad",
1790 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.LessPreciseFPMAD));
1791
1792 if (CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
1793 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("null-pointer-is-valid", "true");
1794 if (!CodeGenOpts.FPDenormalMode.empty())
1795 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("denormal-fp-math", CodeGenOpts.FPDenormalMode);
1796
1797 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-trapping-math",
1798 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.NoTrappingMath));
1799
1800 // Strict (compliant) code is the default, so only add this attribute to
1801 // indicate that we are trying to workaround a problem case.
1802 if (!CodeGenOpts.StrictFloatCastOverflow)
1803 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("strict-float-cast-overflow", "false");
1804
1805 // TODO: Are these all needed?
1806 // unsafe/inf/nan/nsz are handled by instruction-level FastMathFlags.
1807 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-infs-fp-math",
1808 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.NoInfsFPMath));
1809 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-nans-fp-math",
1810 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.NoNaNsFPMath));
1811 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("unsafe-fp-math",
1812 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.UnsafeFPMath));
1813 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("use-soft-float",
1814 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.SoftFloat));
1815 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("stack-protector-buffer-size",
1816 llvm::utostr(CodeGenOpts.SSPBufferSize));
1817 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no-signed-zeros-fp-math",
1818 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.NoSignedZeros));
1819 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(
1820 "correctly-rounded-divide-sqrt-fp-math",
1821 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.CorrectlyRoundedDivSqrt));
1822
1823 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL)
1824 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("denorms-are-zero",
1825 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.FlushDenorm));
1826
1827 // TODO: Reciprocal estimate codegen options should apply to instructions?
1828 const std::vector<std::string> &Recips = CodeGenOpts.Reciprocals;
1829 if (!Recips.empty())
1830 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("reciprocal-estimates",
1831 llvm::join(Recips, ","));
1832
1833 if (!CodeGenOpts.PreferVectorWidth.empty() &&
1834 CodeGenOpts.PreferVectorWidth != "none")
1835 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("prefer-vector-width",
1836 CodeGenOpts.PreferVectorWidth);
1837
1838 if (CodeGenOpts.StackRealignment)
1839 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("stackrealign");
1840 if (CodeGenOpts.Backchain)
1841 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("backchain");
1842
1843 if (CodeGenOpts.SpeculativeLoadHardening)
1844 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening);
1845 }
1846
1847 if (getLangOpts().assumeFunctionsAreConvergent()) {
1848 // Conservatively, mark all functions and calls in CUDA and OpenCL as
1849 // convergent (meaning, they may call an intrinsically convergent op, such
1850 // as __syncthreads() / barrier(), and so can't have certain optimizations
1851 // applied around them). LLVM will remove this attribute where it safely
1852 // can.
1853 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Convergent);
1854 }
1855
1856 if (getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
1857 // Exceptions aren't supported in CUDA device code.
1858 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1859
1860 // Respect -fcuda-flush-denormals-to-zero.
1861 if (CodeGenOpts.FlushDenorm)
1862 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("nvptx-f32ftz", "true");
1863 }
1864
1865 for (StringRef Attr : CodeGenOpts.DefaultFunctionAttrs) {
1866 StringRef Var, Value;
1867 std::tie(Var, Value) = Attr.split('=');
1868 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(Var, Value);
1869 }
1870}
1871
1872void CodeGenModule::AddDefaultFnAttrs(llvm::Function &F) {
1873 llvm::AttrBuilder FuncAttrs;
1874 ConstructDefaultFnAttrList(F.getName(), F.hasOptNone(),
1875 /* AttrOnCallsite = */ false, FuncAttrs);
1876 F.addAttributes(llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, FuncAttrs);
1877}
1878
1879void CodeGenModule::ConstructAttributeList(
1880 StringRef Name, const CGFunctionInfo &FI, CGCalleeInfo CalleeInfo,
1881 llvm::AttributeList &AttrList, unsigned &CallingConv, bool AttrOnCallSite) {
1882 llvm::AttrBuilder FuncAttrs;
1883 llvm::AttrBuilder RetAttrs;
1884
1885 CallingConv = FI.getEffectiveCallingConvention();
1886 if (FI.isNoReturn())
1887 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
1888
1889 // If we have information about the function prototype, we can learn
1890 // attributes from there.
1891 AddAttributesFromFunctionProtoType(getContext(), FuncAttrs,
1892 CalleeInfo.getCalleeFunctionProtoType());
1893
1894 const Decl *TargetDecl = CalleeInfo.getCalleeDecl().getDecl();
1895
1896 bool HasOptnone = false;
1897 // FIXME: handle sseregparm someday...
1898 if (TargetDecl) {
1899 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ReturnsTwiceAttr>())
1900 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReturnsTwice);
1901 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoThrowAttr>())
1902 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1903 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoReturnAttr>())
1904 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
1905 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ColdAttr>())
1906 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Cold);
1907 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoDuplicateAttr>())
1908 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoDuplicate);
1909 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ConvergentAttr>())
1910 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Convergent);
1911
1912 if (const FunctionDecl *Fn = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
1913 AddAttributesFromFunctionProtoType(
1914 getContext(), FuncAttrs, Fn->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>());
1915 // Don't use [[noreturn]] or _Noreturn for a call to a virtual function.
1916 // These attributes are not inherited by overloads.
1917 const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn);
1918 if (Fn->isNoReturn() && !(AttrOnCallSite && MD && MD->isVirtual()))
1919 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
1920 }
1921
1922 // 'const', 'pure' and 'noalias' attributed functions are also nounwind.
1923 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ConstAttr>()) {
1924 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
1925 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1926 } else if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<PureAttr>()) {
1927 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly);
1928 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1929 } else if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoAliasAttr>()) {
1930 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ArgMemOnly);
1931 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1932 }
1933 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<RestrictAttr>())
1934 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
1935 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<ReturnsNonNullAttr>() &&
1936 !CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
1937 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
1938 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<AnyX86NoCallerSavedRegistersAttr>())
1939 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("no_caller_saved_registers");
1940 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<AnyX86NoCfCheckAttr>())
1941 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoCfCheck);
1942
1943 HasOptnone = TargetDecl->hasAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>();
1944 if (auto *AllocSize = TargetDecl->getAttr<AllocSizeAttr>()) {
1945 Optional<unsigned> NumElemsParam;
1946 if (AllocSize->getNumElemsParam().isValid())
1947 NumElemsParam = AllocSize->getNumElemsParam().getLLVMIndex();
1948 FuncAttrs.addAllocSizeAttr(AllocSize->getElemSizeParam().getLLVMIndex(),
1949 NumElemsParam);
1950 }
1951 }
1952
1953 ConstructDefaultFnAttrList(Name, HasOptnone, AttrOnCallSite, FuncAttrs);
1954
1955 // This must run after constructing the default function attribute list
1956 // to ensure that the speculative load hardening attribute is removed
1957 // in the case where the -mspeculative-load-hardening flag was passed.
1958 if (TargetDecl) {
1959 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoSpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr>())
1960 FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening);
1961 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<SpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr>())
1962 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening);
1963 }
1964
1965 if (CodeGenOpts.EnableSegmentedStacks &&
1966 !(TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoSplitStackAttr>()))
1967 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("split-stack");
1968
1969 // Add NonLazyBind attribute to function declarations when -fno-plt
1970 // is used.
1971 if (TargetDecl && CodeGenOpts.NoPLT) {
1972 if (auto *Fn = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
1973 if (!Fn->isDefined() && !AttrOnCallSite) {
1974 FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonLazyBind);
1975 }
1976 }
1977 }
1978
1979 if (TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>()) {
1980 if (getLangOpts().OpenCLVersion <= 120) {
1981 // OpenCL v1.2 Work groups are always uniform
1982 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("uniform-work-group-size", "true");
1983 } else {
1984 // OpenCL v2.0 Work groups may be whether uniform or not.
1985 // '-cl-uniform-work-group-size' compile option gets a hint
1986 // to the compiler that the global work-size be a multiple of
1987 // the work-group size specified to clEnqueueNDRangeKernel
1988 // (i.e. work groups are uniform).
1989 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("uniform-work-group-size",
1990 llvm::toStringRef(CodeGenOpts.UniformWGSize));
1991 }
1992 }
1993
1994 if (!AttrOnCallSite) {
1995 bool DisableTailCalls = false;
1996
1997 if (CodeGenOpts.DisableTailCalls)
1998 DisableTailCalls = true;
1999 else if (TargetDecl) {
2000 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<DisableTailCallsAttr>() ||
2001 TargetDecl->hasAttr<AnyX86InterruptAttr>())
2002 DisableTailCalls = true;
2003 else if (CodeGenOpts.NoEscapingBlockTailCalls) {
2004 if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(TargetDecl))
2005 if (!BD->doesNotEscape())
2006 DisableTailCalls = true;
2007 }
2008 }
2009
2010 FuncAttrs.addAttribute("disable-tail-calls",
2011 llvm::toStringRef(DisableTailCalls));
2012 GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes(CalleeInfo.getCalleeDecl(), FuncAttrs);
2013 }
2014
2015 ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(getContext(), FI);
2016
2017 QualType RetTy = FI.getReturnType();
2018 const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = FI.getReturnInfo();
2019 switch (RetAI.getKind()) {
2020 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2021 if (RetAI.isSignExt())
2022 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SExt);
2023 else
2024 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ZExt);
2025 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2026 case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
2027 if (RetAI.getInReg())
2028 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2029 break;
2030 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
2031 break;
2032
2033 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
2034 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
2035 // inalloca and sret disable readnone and readonly
2036 FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly)
2037 .removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2038 break;
2039 }
2040
2041 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
2042 break;
2043
2044 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
2045 llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
2046 }
2047
2048 if (const auto *RefTy = RetTy->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
2049 QualType PTy = RefTy->getPointeeType();
2050 if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType())
2051 RetAttrs.addDereferenceableAttr(getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(PTy)
2052 .getQuantity());
2053 else if (getTargetCodeGenInfo().canMarkAsNonNull(PTy, Context) &&
2054 !CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
2055 RetAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2056 }
2057
2058 bool hasUsedSRet = false;
2059 SmallVector<llvm::AttributeSet, 4> ArgAttrs(IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
2060
2061 // Attach attributes to sret.
2062 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
2063 llvm::AttrBuilder SRETAttrs;
2064 SRETAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::StructRet);
2065 hasUsedSRet = true;
2066 if (RetAI.getInReg())
2067 SRETAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2068 ArgAttrs[IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo()] =
2069 llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), SRETAttrs);
2070 }
2071
2072 // Attach attributes to inalloca argument.
2073 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg()) {
2074 llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs;
2075 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InAlloca);
2076 ArgAttrs[IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()] =
2077 llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), Attrs);
2078 }
2079
2080 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
2081 for (CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator I = FI.arg_begin(),
2082 E = FI.arg_end();
2083 I != E; ++I, ++ArgNo) {
2084 QualType ParamType = I->type;
2085 const ABIArgInfo &AI = I->info;
2086 llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs;
2087
2088 // Add attribute for padding argument, if necessary.
2089 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasPaddingArg(ArgNo)) {
2090 if (AI.getPaddingInReg()) {
2091 ArgAttrs[IRFunctionArgs.getPaddingArgNo(ArgNo)] =
2092 llvm::AttributeSet::get(
2093 getLLVMContext(),
2094 llvm::AttrBuilder().addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg));
2095 }
2096 }
2097
2098 // 'restrict' -> 'noalias' is done in EmitFunctionProlog when we
2099 // have the corresponding parameter variable. It doesn't make
2100 // sense to do it here because parameters are so messed up.
2101 switch (AI.getKind()) {
2102 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2103 if (AI.isSignExt())
2104 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SExt);
2105 else
2106 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ZExt);
2107 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2108 case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
2109 if (ArgNo == 0 && FI.isChainCall())
2110 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Nest);
2111 else if (AI.getInReg())
2112 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2113 break;
2114
2115 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
2116 if (AI.getInReg())
2117 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InReg);
2118
2119 if (AI.getIndirectByVal())
2120 Attrs.addByValAttr(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ParamType));
2121
2122 CharUnits Align = AI.getIndirectAlign();
2123
2124 // In a byval argument, it is important that the required
2125 // alignment of the type is honored, as LLVM might be creating a
2126 // *new* stack object, and needs to know what alignment to give
2127 // it. (Sometimes it can deduce a sensible alignment on its own,
2128 // but not if clang decides it must emit a packed struct, or the
2129 // user specifies increased alignment requirements.)
2130 //
2131 // This is different from indirect *not* byval, where the object
2132 // exists already, and the align attribute is purely
2133 // informative.
2134 assert(!Align.isZero());
2135
2136 // For now, only add this when we have a byval argument.
2137 // TODO: be less lazy about updating test cases.
2138 if (AI.getIndirectByVal())
2139 Attrs.addAlignmentAttr(Align.getQuantity());
2140
2141 // byval disables readnone and readonly.
2142 FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly)
2143 .removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2144 break;
2145 }
2146 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
2147 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
2148 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
2149 break;
2150
2151 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
2152 // inalloca disables readnone and readonly.
2153 FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly)
2154 .removeAttribute(llvm::Attribute::ReadNone);
2155 continue;
2156 }
2157
2158 if (const auto *RefTy = ParamType->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
2159 QualType PTy = RefTy->getPointeeType();
2160 if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType())
2161 Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(PTy)
2162 .getQuantity());
2163 else if (getTargetCodeGenInfo().canMarkAsNonNull(PTy, Context) &&
2164 !CodeGenOpts.NullPointerIsValid)
2165 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2166 }
2167
2168 switch (FI.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).getABI()) {
2169 case ParameterABI::Ordinary:
2170 break;
2171
2172 case ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult: {
2173 // Add 'sret' if we haven't already used it for something, but
2174 // only if the result is void.
2175 if (!hasUsedSRet && RetTy->isVoidType()) {
2176 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::StructRet);
2177 hasUsedSRet = true;
2178 }
2179
2180 // Add 'noalias' in either case.
2181 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2182
2183 // Add 'dereferenceable' and 'alignment'.
2184 auto PTy = ParamType->getPointeeType();
2185 if (!PTy->isIncompleteType() && PTy->isConstantSizeType()) {
2186 auto info = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(PTy);
2187 Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(info.first.getQuantity());
2188 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::getWithAlignment(getLLVMContext(),
2189 info.second.getQuantity()));
2190 }
2191 break;
2192 }
2193
2194 case ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult:
2195 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SwiftError);
2196 break;
2197
2198 case ParameterABI::SwiftContext:
2199 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::SwiftSelf);
2200 break;
2201 }
2202
2203 if (FI.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).isNoEscape())
2204 Attrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoCapture);
2205
2206 if (Attrs.hasAttributes()) {
2207 unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
2208 std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
2209 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumIRArgs; i++)
2210 ArgAttrs[FirstIRArg + i] =
2211 llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), Attrs);
2212 }
2213 }
2214 assert(ArgNo == FI.arg_size());
2215
2216 AttrList = llvm::AttributeList::get(
2217 getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), FuncAttrs),
2218 llvm::AttributeSet::get(getLLVMContext(), RetAttrs), ArgAttrs);
2219}

2221/// An argument came in as a promoted argument; demote it back to its
2222/// declared type.
2223static llvm::Value *emitArgumentDemotion(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2224 const VarDecl *var,
2225 llvm::Value *value) {
2226 llvm::Type *varType = CGF.ConvertType(var->getType());
2227
2228 // This can happen with promotions that actually don't change the
2229 // underlying type, like the enum promotions.
2230 if (value->getType() == varType) return value;
2231
2232 assert((varType->isIntegerTy() || varType->isFloatingPointTy())
2233 && "unexpected promotion type");
2234
2235 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(varType))
2236 return CGF.Builder.CreateTrunc(value, varType, "arg.unpromote");
2237
2238 return CGF.Builder.CreateFPCast(value, varType, "arg.unpromote");
2239}
2240
2241/// Returns the attribute (either parameter attribute, or function
2242/// attribute), which declares argument ArgNo to be non-null.
2243static const NonNullAttr *getNonNullAttr(const Decl *FD, const ParmVarDecl *PVD,
2244 QualType ArgType, unsigned ArgNo) {
2245 // FIXME: __attribute__((nonnull)) can also be applied to:
2246 // - references to pointers, where the pointee is known to be
2247 // nonnull (apparently a Clang extension)
2248 // - transparent unions containing pointers
2249 // In the former case, LLVM IR cannot represent the constraint. In
2250 // the latter case, we have no guarantee that the transparent union
2251 // is in fact passed as a pointer.
2252 if (!ArgType->isAnyPointerType() && !ArgType->isBlockPointerType())
2253 return nullptr;
2254 // First, check attribute on parameter itself.
2255 if (PVD) {
2256 if (auto ParmNNAttr = PVD->getAttr<NonNullAttr>())
2257 return ParmNNAttr;
2258 }
2259 // Check function attributes.
2260 if (!FD)
2261 return nullptr;
2262 for (const auto *NNAttr : FD->specific_attrs<NonNullAttr>()) {
2263 if (NNAttr->isNonNull(ArgNo))
2264 return NNAttr;
2265 }
2266 return nullptr;
2267}

2269namespace {
2270 struct CopyBackSwiftError final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
2271 Address Temp;
2272 Address Arg;
2273 CopyBackSwiftError(Address temp, Address arg) : Temp(temp), Arg(arg) {}
2274 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
2275 llvm::Value *errorValue = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Temp);
2276 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(errorValue, Arg);
2277 }
2278 };
2279}
2280
2281void CodeGenFunction::EmitFunctionProlog(const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
2282 llvm::Function *Fn,
2283 const FunctionArgList &Args) {
2284 if (CurCodeDecl && CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<NakedAttr>())
2285 // Naked functions don't have prologues.
2286 return;
2287
2288 // If this is an implicit-return-zero function, go ahead and
2289 // initialize the return value. TODO: it might be nice to have
2290 // a more general mechanism for this that didn't require synthesized
2291 // return statements.
2292 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(CurCodeDecl)) {
2293 if (FD->hasImplicitReturnZero()) {
2294 QualType RetTy = FD->getReturnType().getUnqualifiedType();
2295 llvm::Type* LLVMTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(RetTy);
2296 llvm::Constant* Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(LLVMTy);
2297 Builder.CreateStore(Zero, ReturnValue);
2298 }
2299 }
2300
2301 // FIXME: We no longer need the types from FunctionArgList; lift up and
2302 // simplify.
2303
2304 ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(CGM.getContext(), FI);
2305 // Flattened function arguments.
2306 SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 16> FnArgs;
2307 FnArgs.reserve(IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
2308 for (auto &Arg : Fn->args()) {
2309 FnArgs.push_back(&Arg);
2310 }
2311 assert(FnArgs.size() == IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
2312
2313 // If we're using inalloca, all the memory arguments are GEPs off of the last
2314 // parameter, which is a pointer to the complete memory area.
2315 Address ArgStruct = Address::invalid();
2316 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg()) {
2317 ArgStruct = Address(FnArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()],
2318 FI.getArgStructAlignment());
2319
2320 assert(ArgStruct.getType() == FI.getArgStruct()->getPointerTo(CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()));
2321 }
2322
2323 // Name the struct return parameter.
2324 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
2325 auto AI = cast<llvm::Argument>(FnArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo()]);
2326 AI->setName("agg.result");
2327 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2328 }
2329
2330 // Track if we received the parameter as a pointer (indirect, byval, or
2331 // inalloca). If already have a pointer, EmitParmDecl doesn't need to copy it
2332 // into a local alloca for us.
2333 SmallVector<ParamValue, 16> ArgVals;
2334 ArgVals.reserve(Args.size());
2335
2336 // Create a pointer value for every parameter declaration. This usually
2337 // entails copying one or more LLVM IR arguments into an alloca. Don't push
2338 // any cleanups or do anything that might unwind. We do that separately, so
2339 // we can push the cleanups in the correct order for the ABI.
2340 assert(FI.arg_size() == Args.size() &&
2341 "Mismatch between function signature & arguments.");
2342 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
2343 CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator info_it = FI.arg_begin();
2344 for (FunctionArgList::const_iterator i = Args.begin(), e = Args.end();
2345 i != e; ++i, ++info_it, ++ArgNo) {
2346 const VarDecl *Arg = *i;
2347 const ABIArgInfo &ArgI = info_it->info;
2348
2349 bool isPromoted =
2350 isa<ParmVarDecl>(Arg) && cast<ParmVarDecl>(Arg)->isKNRPromoted();
2351 // We are converting from ABIArgInfo type to VarDecl type directly, unless
2352 // the parameter is promoted. In this case we convert to
2353 // CGFunctionInfo::ArgInfo type with subsequent argument demotion.
2354 QualType Ty = isPromoted ? info_it->type : Arg->getType();
2355 assert(hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty) ==
2356 hasScalarEvaluationKind(Arg->getType()));
2357
2358 unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
2359 std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
2360
2361 switch (ArgI.getKind()) {
2362 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca: {
2363 assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
2364 auto FieldIndex = ArgI.getInAllocaFieldIndex();
2365 Address V =
2366 Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgStruct, FieldIndex, Arg->getName());
2367 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(V));
2368 break;
2369 }
2370
2371 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
2372 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2373 Address ParamAddr = Address(FnArgs[FirstIRArg], ArgI.getIndirectAlign());
2374
2375 if (!hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
2376 // Aggregates and complex variables are accessed by reference. All we
2377 // need to do is realign the value, if requested.
2378 Address V = ParamAddr;
2379 if (ArgI.getIndirectRealign()) {
2380 Address AlignedTemp = CreateMemTemp(Ty, "coerce");
2381
2382 // Copy from the incoming argument pointer to the temporary with the
2383 // appropriate alignment.
2384 //
2385 // FIXME: We should have a common utility for generating an aggregate
2386 // copy.
2387 CharUnits Size = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty);
2388 auto SizeVal = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, Size.getQuantity());
2389 Address Dst = Builder.CreateBitCast(AlignedTemp, Int8PtrTy);
2390 Address Src = Builder.CreateBitCast(ParamAddr, Int8PtrTy);
2391 Builder.CreateMemCpy(Dst, Src, SizeVal, false);
2392 V = AlignedTemp;
2393 }
2394 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(V));
2395 } else {
2396 // Load scalar value from indirect argument.
2397 llvm::Value *V =
2398 EmitLoadOfScalar(ParamAddr, false, Ty, Arg->getBeginLoc());
2399
2400 if (isPromoted)
2401 V = emitArgumentDemotion(*this, Arg, V);
2402 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(V));
2403 }
2404 break;
2405 }
2406
2407 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2408 case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
2409
2410 // If we have the trivial case, handle it with no muss and fuss.
2411 if (!isa<llvm::StructType>(ArgI.getCoerceToType()) &&
2412 ArgI.getCoerceToType() == ConvertType(Ty) &&
2413 ArgI.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
2414 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2415 llvm::Value *V = FnArgs[FirstIRArg];
2416 auto AI = cast<llvm::Argument>(V);
2417
2418 if (const ParmVarDecl *PVD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(Arg)) {
2419 if (getNonNullAttr(CurCodeDecl, PVD, PVD->getType(),
2420 PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex()) &&
2421 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NullPointerIsValid)
2422 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2423
2424 QualType OTy = PVD->getOriginalType();
2425 if (const auto *ArrTy =
2426 getContext().getAsConstantArrayType(OTy)) {
2427 // A C99 array parameter declaration with the static keyword also
2428 // indicates dereferenceability, and if the size is constant we can
2429 // use the dereferenceable attribute (which requires the size in
2430 // bytes).
2431 if (ArrTy->getSizeModifier() == ArrayType::Static) {
2432 QualType ETy = ArrTy->getElementType();
2433 uint64_t ArrSize = ArrTy->getSize().getZExtValue();
2434 if (!ETy->isIncompleteType() && ETy->isConstantSizeType() &&
2435 ArrSize) {
2436 llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs;
2437 Attrs.addDereferenceableAttr(
2438 getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ETy).getQuantity()*ArrSize);
2439 AI->addAttrs(Attrs);
2440 } else if (CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().canMarkAsNonNull(ETy, getContext()) &&
2441 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NullPointerIsValid) {
2442 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2443 }
2444 }
2445 } else if (const auto *ArrTy =
2446 getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(OTy)) {
2447 // For C99 VLAs with the static keyword, we don't know the size so
2448 // we can't use the dereferenceable attribute, but in addrspace(0)
2449 // we know that it must be nonnull.
2450 if (ArrTy->getSizeModifier() == VariableArrayType::Static &&
2451 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().canMarkAsNonNull(ArrTy->getElementType(),
2452 getContext()) &&
2453 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NullPointerIsValid)
2454 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NonNull);
2455 }
2456
2457 const auto *AVAttr = PVD->getAttr<AlignValueAttr>();
2458 if (!AVAttr)
2459 if (const auto *TOTy = dyn_cast<TypedefType>(OTy))
2460 AVAttr = TOTy->getDecl()->getAttr<AlignValueAttr>();
2461 if (AVAttr && !SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment)) {
2462 // If alignment-assumption sanitizer is enabled, we do *not* add
2463 // alignment attribute here, but emit normal alignment assumption,
2464 // so the UBSAN check could function.
2465 llvm::Value *AlignmentValue =
2466 EmitScalarExpr(AVAttr->getAlignment());
2467 llvm::ConstantInt *AlignmentCI =
2468 cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(AlignmentValue);
2469 unsigned Alignment = std::min((unsigned)AlignmentCI->getZExtValue(),
2470 +llvm::Value::MaximumAlignment);
2471 AI->addAttrs(llvm::AttrBuilder().addAlignmentAttr(Alignment));
2472 }
2473 }
2474
2475 if (Arg->getType().isRestrictQualified())
2476 AI->addAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
2477
2478 // LLVM expects swifterror parameters to be used in very restricted
2479 // ways. Copy the value into a less-restricted temporary.
2480 if (FI.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).getABI()
2481 == ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult) {
2482 QualType pointeeTy = Ty->getPointeeType();
2483 assert(pointeeTy->isPointerType());
2484 Address temp =
2485 CreateMemTemp(pointeeTy, getPointerAlign(), "swifterror.temp");
2486 Address arg = Address(V, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(pointeeTy));
2487 llvm::Value *incomingErrorValue = Builder.CreateLoad(arg);
2488 Builder.CreateStore(incomingErrorValue, temp);
2489 V = temp.getPointer();
2490
2491 // Push a cleanup to copy the value back at the end of the function.
2492 // The convention does not guarantee that the value will be written
2493 // back if the function exits with an unwind exception.
2494 EHStack.pushCleanup<CopyBackSwiftError>(NormalCleanup, temp, arg);
2495 }
2496
2497 // Ensure the argument is the correct type.
2498 if (V->getType() != ArgI.getCoerceToType())
2499 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, ArgI.getCoerceToType());
2500
2501 if (isPromoted)
2502 V = emitArgumentDemotion(*this, Arg, V);
2503
2504 // Because of merging of function types from multiple decls it is
2505 // possible for the type of an argument to not match the corresponding
2506 // type in the function type. Since we are codegening the callee
2507 // in here, add a cast to the argument type.
2508 llvm::Type *LTy = ConvertType(Arg->getType());
2509 if (V->getType() != LTy)
2510 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, LTy);
2511
2512 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(V));
2513 break;
2514 }
2515
2516 Address Alloca = CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getDeclAlign(Arg),
2517 Arg->getName());
2518
2519 // Pointer to store into.
2520 Address Ptr = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, Alloca, ArgI);
2521
2522 // Fast-isel and the optimizer generally like scalar values better than
2523 // FCAs, so we flatten them if this is safe to do for this argument.
2524 llvm::StructType *STy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(ArgI.getCoerceToType());
2525 if (ArgI.isDirect() && ArgI.getCanBeFlattened() && STy &&
2526 STy->getNumElements() > 1) {
2527 uint64_t SrcSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(STy);
2528 llvm::Type *DstTy = Ptr.getElementType();
2529 uint64_t DstSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(DstTy);
2530
2531 Address AddrToStoreInto = Address::invalid();
2532 if (SrcSize <= DstSize) {
2533 AddrToStoreInto = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Ptr, STy);
2534 } else {
2535 AddrToStoreInto =
2536 CreateTempAlloca(STy, Alloca.getAlignment(), "coerce");
2537 }
2538
2539 assert(STy->getNumElements() == NumIRArgs);
2540 for (unsigned i = 0, e = STy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
2541 auto AI = FnArgs[FirstIRArg + i];
2542 AI->setName(Arg->getName() + ".coerce" + Twine(i));
2543 Address EltPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(AddrToStoreInto, i);
2544 Builder.CreateStore(AI, EltPtr);
2545 }
2546
2547 if (SrcSize > DstSize) {
2548 Builder.CreateMemCpy(Ptr, AddrToStoreInto, DstSize);
2549 }
2550
2551 } else {
2552 // Simple case, just do a coerced store of the argument into the alloca.
2553 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
2554 auto AI = FnArgs[FirstIRArg];
2555 AI->setName(Arg->getName() + ".coerce");
2556 CreateCoercedStore(AI, Ptr, /*DestIsVolatile=*/false, *this);
2557 }
2558
2559 // Match to what EmitParmDecl is expecting for this type.
2560 if (CodeGenFunction::hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
2561 llvm::Value *V =
2562 EmitLoadOfScalar(Alloca, false, Ty, Arg->getBeginLoc());
2563 if (isPromoted)
2564 V = emitArgumentDemotion(*this, Arg, V);
2565 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(V));
2566 } else {
2567 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(Alloca));
2568 }
2569 break;
2570 }
2571
2572 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
2573 // Reconstruct into a temporary.
2574 Address alloca = CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getDeclAlign(Arg));
2575 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(alloca));
2576
2577 auto coercionType = ArgI.getCoerceAndExpandType();
2578 alloca = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(alloca, coercionType);
2579
2580 unsigned argIndex = FirstIRArg;
2581 for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
2582 llvm::Type *eltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
2583 if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(eltType))
2584 continue;
2585
2586 auto eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(alloca, i);
2587 auto elt = FnArgs[argIndex++];
2588 Builder.CreateStore(elt, eltAddr);
2589 }
2590 assert(argIndex == FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
2591 break;
2592 }
2593
2594 case ABIArgInfo::Expand: {
2595 // If this structure was expanded into multiple arguments then
2596 // we need to create a temporary and reconstruct it from the
2597 // arguments.
2598 Address Alloca = CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getDeclAlign(Arg));
2599 LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Alloca, Ty);
2600 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(Alloca));
2601
2602 auto FnArgIter = FnArgs.begin() + FirstIRArg;
2603 ExpandTypeFromArgs(Ty, LV, FnArgIter);
2604 assert(FnArgIter == FnArgs.begin() + FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
2605 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumIRArgs; i != e; ++i) {
2606 auto AI = FnArgs[FirstIRArg + i];
2607 AI->setName(Arg->getName() + "." + Twine(i));
2608 }
2609 break;
2610 }
2611
2612 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
2613 assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
2614 // Initialize the local variable appropriately.
2615 if (!hasScalarEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
2616 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forIndirect(CreateMemTemp(Ty)));
2617 } else {
2618 llvm::Value *U = llvm::UndefValue::get(ConvertType(Arg->getType()));
2619 ArgVals.push_back(ParamValue::forDirect(U));
2620 }
2621 break;
2622 }
2623 }
2624
2625 if (getTarget().getCXXABI().areArgsDestroyedLeftToRightInCallee()) {
2626 for (int I = Args.size() - 1; I >= 0; --I)
2627 EmitParmDecl(*Args[I], ArgVals[I], I + 1);
2628 } else {
2629 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Args.size(); I != E; ++I)
2630 EmitParmDecl(*Args[I], ArgVals[I], I + 1);
2631 }
2632}
2633
2634static void eraseUnusedBitCasts(llvm::Instruction *insn) {
2635 while (insn->use_empty()) {
2636 llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(insn);
2637 if (!bitcast) return;
2638
2639 // This is "safe" because we would have used a ConstantExpr otherwise.
2640 insn = cast<llvm::Instruction>(bitcast->getOperand(0));
2641 bitcast->eraseFromParent();
2642 }
2643}
2644
2645/// Try to emit a fused autorelease of a return result.
2646static llvm::Value *tryEmitFusedAutoreleaseOfResult(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2647 llvm::Value *result) {
2648 // We must be immediately followed the cast.
2649 llvm::BasicBlock *BB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2650 if (BB->empty()) return nullptr;
2651 if (&BB->back() != result) return nullptr;
2652
2653 llvm::Type *resultType = result->getType();
2654
2655 // result is in a BasicBlock and is therefore an Instruction.
2656 llvm::Instruction *generator = cast<llvm::Instruction>(result);
2657
2658 SmallVector<llvm::Instruction *, 4> InstsToKill;
2659
2660 // Look for:
2661 // %generator = bitcast %type1* %generator2 to %type2*
2662 while (llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(generator)) {
2663 // We would have emitted this as a constant if the operand weren't
2664 // an Instruction.
2665 generator = cast<llvm::Instruction>(bitcast->getOperand(0));
2666
2667 // Require the generator to be immediately followed by the cast.
2668 if (generator->getNextNode() != bitcast)
2669 return nullptr;
2670
2671 InstsToKill.push_back(bitcast);
2672 }
2673
2674 // Look for:
2675 // %generator = call i8* @objc_retain(i8* %originalResult)
2676 // or
2677 // %generator = call i8* @objc_retainAutoreleasedReturnValue(i8* %originalResult)
2678 llvm::CallInst *call = dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(generator);
2679 if (!call) return nullptr;
2680
2681 bool doRetainAutorelease;
2682
2683 if (call->getCalledValue() == CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_retain) {
2684 doRetainAutorelease = true;
2685 } else if (call->getCalledValue() == CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints()
2686 .objc_retainAutoreleasedReturnValue) {
2687 doRetainAutorelease = false;
2688
2689 // If we emitted an assembly marker for this call (and the
2690 // ARCEntrypoints field should have been set if so), go looking
2691 // for that call. If we can't find it, we can't do this
2692 // optimization. But it should always be the immediately previous
2693 // instruction, unless we needed bitcasts around the call.
2694 if (CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().retainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker) {
2695 llvm::Instruction *prev = call->getPrevNode();
2696 assert(prev);
2697 if (isa<llvm::BitCastInst>(prev)) {
2698 prev = prev->getPrevNode();
2699 assert(prev);
2700 }
2701 assert(isa<llvm::CallInst>(prev));
2702 assert(cast<llvm::CallInst>(prev)->getCalledValue() ==
2703 CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().retainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker);
2704 InstsToKill.push_back(prev);
2705 }
2706 } else {
2707 return nullptr;
2708 }
2709
2710 result = call->getArgOperand(0);
2711 InstsToKill.push_back(call);
2712
2713 // Keep killing bitcasts, for sanity. Note that we no longer care
2714 // about precise ordering as long as there's exactly one use.
2715 while (llvm::BitCastInst *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::BitCastInst>(result)) {
2716 if (!bitcast->hasOneUse()) break;
2717 InstsToKill.push_back(bitcast);
2718 result = bitcast->getOperand(0);
2719 }
2720
2721 // Delete all the unnecessary instructions, from latest to earliest.
2722 for (auto *I : InstsToKill)
2723 I->eraseFromParent();
2724
2725 // Do the fused retain/autorelease if we were asked to.
2726 if (doRetainAutorelease)
2727 result = CGF.EmitARCRetainAutoreleaseReturnValue(result);
2728
2729 // Cast back to the result type.
2730 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(result, resultType);
2731}
2732
2733/// If this is a +1 of the value of an immutable 'self', remove it.
2734static llvm::Value *tryRemoveRetainOfSelf(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2735 llvm::Value *result) {
2736 // This is only applicable to a method with an immutable 'self'.
2737 const ObjCMethodDecl *method =
2738 dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMethodDecl>(CGF.CurCodeDecl);
2739 if (!method) return nullptr;
2740 const VarDecl *self = method->getSelfDecl();
2741 if (!self->getType().isConstQualified()) return nullptr;
2742
2743 // Look for a retain call.
2744 llvm::CallInst *retainCall =
2745 dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(result->stripPointerCasts());
2746 if (!retainCall ||
2747 retainCall->getCalledValue() != CGF.CGM.getObjCEntrypoints().objc_retain)
2748 return nullptr;
2749
2750 // Look for an ordinary load of 'self'.
2751 llvm::Value *retainedValue = retainCall->getArgOperand(0);
2752 llvm::LoadInst *load =
2753 dyn_cast<llvm::LoadInst>(retainedValue->stripPointerCasts());
2754 if (!load || load->isAtomic() || load->isVolatile() ||
2755 load->getPointerOperand() != CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(self).getPointer())
2756 return nullptr;
2757
2758 // Okay! Burn it all down. This relies for correctness on the
2759 // assumption that the retain is emitted as part of the return and
2760 // that thereafter everything is used "linearly".
2761 llvm::Type *resultType = result->getType();
2762 eraseUnusedBitCasts(cast<llvm::Instruction>(result));
2763 assert(retainCall->use_empty());
2764 retainCall->eraseFromParent();
2765 eraseUnusedBitCasts(cast<llvm::Instruction>(retainedValue));
2766
2767 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(load, resultType);
2768}
2769
2770/// Emit an ARC autorelease of the result of a function.
2771///
2772/// \return the value to actually return from the function
2773static llvm::Value *emitAutoreleaseOfResult(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2774 llvm::Value *result) {
2775 // If we're returning 'self', kill the initial retain. This is a
2776 // heuristic attempt to "encourage correctness" in the really unfortunate
2777 // case where we have a return of self during a dealloc and we desperately
2778 // need to avoid the possible autorelease.
2779 if (llvm::Value *self = tryRemoveRetainOfSelf(CGF, result))
2780 return self;
2781
2782 // At -O0, try to emit a fused retain/autorelease.
2783 if (CGF.shouldUseFusedARCCalls())
2784 if (llvm::Value *fused = tryEmitFusedAutoreleaseOfResult(CGF, result))
2785 return fused;
2786
2787 return CGF.EmitARCAutoreleaseReturnValue(result);
2788}
2789
2790/// Heuristically search for a dominating store to the return-value slot.
2791static llvm::StoreInst *findDominatingStoreToReturnValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
2792 // Check if a User is a store which pointerOperand is the ReturnValue.
2793 // We are looking for stores to the ReturnValue, not for stores of the
2794 // ReturnValue to some other location.
2795 auto GetStoreIfValid = [&CGF](llvm::User *U) -> llvm::StoreInst * {
2796 auto *SI = dyn_cast<llvm::StoreInst>(U);
2797 if (!SI || SI->getPointerOperand() != CGF.ReturnValue.getPointer())
2798 return nullptr;
2799 // These aren't actually possible for non-coerced returns, and we
2800 // only care about non-coerced returns on this code path.
2801 assert(!SI->isAtomic() && !SI->isVolatile());
2802 return SI;
2803 };
2804 // If there are multiple uses of the return-value slot, just check
2805 // for something immediately preceding the IP. Sometimes this can
2806 // happen with how we generate implicit-returns; it can also happen
2807 // with noreturn cleanups.
2808 if (!CGF.ReturnValue.getPointer()->hasOneUse()) {
2809 llvm::BasicBlock *IP = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2810 if (IP->empty()) return nullptr;
2811 llvm::Instruction *I = &IP->back();
2812
2813 // Skip lifetime markers
2814 for (llvm::BasicBlock::reverse_iterator II = IP->rbegin(),
2815 IE = IP->rend();
2816 II != IE; ++II) {
2817 if (llvm::IntrinsicInst *Intrinsic =
2818 dyn_cast<llvm::IntrinsicInst>(&*II)) {
2819 if (Intrinsic->getIntrinsicID() == llvm::Intrinsic::lifetime_end) {
2820 const llvm::Value *CastAddr = Intrinsic->getArgOperand(1);
2821 ++II;
2822 if (II == IE)
2823 break;
2824 if (isa<llvm::BitCastInst>(&*II) && (CastAddr == &*II))
2825 continue;
2826 }
2827 }
2828 I = &*II;
2829 break;
2830 }
2831
2832 return GetStoreIfValid(I);
2833 }
2834
2835 llvm::StoreInst *store =
2836 GetStoreIfValid(CGF.ReturnValue.getPointer()->user_back());
2837 if (!store) return nullptr;
2838
2839 // Now do a first-and-dirty dominance check: just walk up the
2840 // single-predecessors chain from the current insertion point.
2841 llvm::BasicBlock *StoreBB = store->getParent();
2842 llvm::BasicBlock *IP = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2843 while (IP != StoreBB) {
2844 if (!(IP = IP->getSinglePredecessor()))
2845 return nullptr;
2846 }
2847
2848 // Okay, the store's basic block dominates the insertion point; we
2849 // can do our thing.
2850 return store;
2851}
2852
2853void CodeGenFunction::EmitFunctionEpilog(const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
2854 bool EmitRetDbgLoc,
2855 SourceLocation EndLoc) {
2856 if (FI.isNoReturn()) {
2857 // Noreturn functions don't return.
2858 EmitUnreachable(EndLoc);
2859 return;
2860 }
2861
2862 if (CurCodeDecl && CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<NakedAttr>()) {
2863 // Naked functions don't have epilogues.
2864 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
2865 return;
2866 }
2867
2868 // Functions with no result always return void.
2869 if (!ReturnValue.isValid()) {
2870 Builder.CreateRetVoid();
2871 return;
2872 }
2873
2874 llvm::DebugLoc RetDbgLoc;
2875 llvm::Value *RV = nullptr;
2876 QualType RetTy = FI.getReturnType();
2877 const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = FI.getReturnInfo();
2878
2879 switch (RetAI.getKind()) {
2880 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
2881 // Aggregrates get evaluated directly into the destination. Sometimes we
2882 // need to return the sret value in a register, though.
2883 assert(hasAggregateEvaluationKind(RetTy));
2884 if (RetAI.getInAllocaSRet()) {
2885 llvm::Function::arg_iterator EI = CurFn->arg_end();
2886 --EI;
2887 llvm::Value *ArgStruct = &*EI;
2888 llvm::Value *SRet = Builder.CreateStructGEP(
2889 nullptr, ArgStruct, RetAI.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
2890 RV = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(SRet, getPointerAlign(), "sret");
2891 }
2892 break;
2893
2894 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
2895 auto AI = CurFn->arg_begin();
2896 if (RetAI.isSRetAfterThis())
2897 ++AI;
2898 switch (getEvaluationKind(RetTy)) {
2899 case TEK_Complex: {
2900 ComplexPairTy RT =
2901 EmitLoadOfComplex(MakeAddrLValue(ReturnValue, RetTy), EndLoc);
2902 EmitStoreOfComplex(RT, MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(&*AI, RetTy),
2903 /*isInit*/ true);
2904 break;
2905 }
2906 case TEK_Aggregate:
2907 // Do nothing; aggregrates get evaluated directly into the destination.
2908 break;
2909 case TEK_Scalar:
2910 EmitStoreOfScalar(Builder.CreateLoad(ReturnValue),
2911 MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(&*AI, RetTy),
2912 /*isInit*/ true);
2913 break;
2914 }
2915 break;
2916 }
2917
2918 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
2919 case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
2920 if (RetAI.getCoerceToType() == ConvertType(RetTy) &&
2921 RetAI.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
2922 // The internal return value temp always will have pointer-to-return-type
2923 // type, just do a load.
2924
2925 // If there is a dominating store to ReturnValue, we can elide
2926 // the load, zap the store, and usually zap the alloca.
2927 if (llvm::StoreInst *SI =
2928 findDominatingStoreToReturnValue(*this)) {
2929 // Reuse the debug location from the store unless there is
2930 // cleanup code to be emitted between the store and return
2931 // instruction.
2932 if (EmitRetDbgLoc && !AutoreleaseResult)
2933 RetDbgLoc = SI->getDebugLoc();
2934 // Get the stored value and nuke the now-dead store.
2935 RV = SI->getValueOperand();
2936 SI->eraseFromParent();
2937
2938 // Otherwise, we have to do a simple load.
2939 } else {
2940 RV = Builder.CreateLoad(ReturnValue);
2941 }
2942 } else {
2943 // If the value is offset in memory, apply the offset now.
2944 Address V = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, ReturnValue, RetAI);
2945
2946 RV = CreateCoercedLoad(V, RetAI.getCoerceToType(), *this);
2947 }
2948
2949 // In ARC, end functions that return a retainable type with a call
2950 // to objc_autoreleaseReturnValue.
2951 if (AutoreleaseResult) {
2952#ifndef NDEBUG
2953 // Type::isObjCRetainabletype has to be called on a QualType that hasn't
2954 // been stripped of the typedefs, so we cannot use RetTy here. Get the
2955 // original return type of FunctionDecl, CurCodeDecl, and BlockDecl from
2956 // CurCodeDecl or BlockInfo.
2957 QualType RT;
2958
2959 if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
2960 RT = FD->getReturnType();
2961 else if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
2962 RT = MD->getReturnType();
2963 else if (isa<BlockDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
2964 RT = BlockInfo->BlockExpression->getFunctionType()->getReturnType();
2965 else
2966 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected function/method type");
2967
2968 assert(getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
2969 !FI.isReturnsRetained() &&
2970 RT->isObjCRetainableType());
2971#endif
2972 RV = emitAutoreleaseOfResult(*this, RV);
2973 }
2974
2975 break;
2976
2977 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
2978 break;
2979
2980 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
2981 auto coercionType = RetAI.getCoerceAndExpandType();
2982
2983 // Load all of the coerced elements out into results.
2984 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value*, 4> results;
2985 Address addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(ReturnValue, coercionType);
2986 for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
2987 auto coercedEltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
2988 if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(coercedEltType))
2989 continue;
2990
2991 auto eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, i);
2992 auto elt = Builder.CreateLoad(eltAddr);
2993 results.push_back(elt);
2994 }
2995
2996 // If we have one result, it's the single direct result type.
2997 if (results.size() == 1) {
2998 RV = results[0];
2999
3000 // Otherwise, we need to make a first-class aggregate.
3001 } else {
3002 // Construct a return type that lacks padding elements.
3003 llvm::Type *returnType = RetAI.getUnpaddedCoerceAndExpandType();
3004
3005 RV = llvm::UndefValue::get(returnType);
3006 for (unsigned i = 0, e = results.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3007 RV = Builder.CreateInsertValue(RV, results[i], i);
3008 }
3009 }
3010 break;
3011 }
3012
3013 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
3014 llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
3015 }
3016
3017 llvm::Instruction *Ret;
3018 if (RV) {
3019 EmitReturnValueCheck(RV);
3020 Ret = Builder.CreateRet(RV);
3021 } else {
3022 Ret = Builder.CreateRetVoid();
3023 }
3024
3025 if (RetDbgLoc)
3026 Ret->setDebugLoc(std::move(RetDbgLoc));
3027}
3028
3029void CodeGenFunction::EmitReturnValueCheck(llvm::Value *RV) {
3030 // A current decl may not be available when emitting vtable thunks.
3031 if (!CurCodeDecl)
3032 return;
3033
3034 ReturnsNonNullAttr *RetNNAttr = nullptr;
3035 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ReturnsNonnullAttribute))
3036 RetNNAttr = CurCodeDecl->getAttr<ReturnsNonNullAttr>();
3037
3038 if (!RetNNAttr && !requiresReturnValueNullabilityCheck())
3039 return;
3040
3041 // Prefer the returns_nonnull attribute if it's present.
3042 SourceLocation AttrLoc;
3043 SanitizerMask CheckKind;
3044 SanitizerHandler Handler;
3045 if (RetNNAttr) {
3046 assert(!requiresReturnValueNullabilityCheck() &&
3047 "Cannot check nullability and the nonnull attribute");
3048 AttrLoc = RetNNAttr->getLocation();
3049 CheckKind = SanitizerKind::ReturnsNonnullAttribute;
3050 Handler = SanitizerHandler::NonnullReturn;
3051 } else {
3052 if (auto *DD = dyn_cast<DeclaratorDecl>(CurCodeDecl))
3053 if (auto *TSI = DD->getTypeSourceInfo())
3054 if (auto FTL = TSI->getTypeLoc().castAs<FunctionTypeLoc>())
3055 AttrLoc = FTL.getReturnLoc().findNullabilityLoc();
3056 CheckKind = SanitizerKind::NullabilityReturn;
3057 Handler = SanitizerHandler::NullabilityReturn;
3058 }
3059
3060 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
3061
3062 // Make sure the "return" source location is valid. If we're checking a
3063 // nullability annotation, make sure the preconditions for the check are met.
3064 llvm::BasicBlock *Check = createBasicBlock("nullcheck");
3065 llvm::BasicBlock *NoCheck = createBasicBlock("no.nullcheck");
3066 llvm::Value *SLocPtr = Builder.CreateLoad(ReturnLocation, "return.sloc.load");
3067 llvm::Value *CanNullCheck = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(SLocPtr);
3068 if (requiresReturnValueNullabilityCheck())
3069 CanNullCheck =
3070 Builder.CreateAnd(CanNullCheck, RetValNullabilityPrecondition);
3071 Builder.CreateCondBr(CanNullCheck, Check, NoCheck);
3072 EmitBlock(Check);
3073
3074 // Now do the null check.
3075 llvm::Value *Cond = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(RV);
3076 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(AttrLoc)};
3077 llvm::Value *DynamicData[] = {SLocPtr};
3078 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Cond, CheckKind), Handler, StaticData, DynamicData);
3079
3080 EmitBlock(NoCheck);
3081
3082#ifndef NDEBUG
3083 // The return location should not be used after the check has been emitted.
3084 ReturnLocation = Address::invalid();
3085#endif
3086}

3088static bool isInAllocaArgument(CGCXXABI &ABI, QualType type) {
3089 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = type->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3090 return RD && ABI.getRecordArgABI(RD) == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory;

3096 // placeholders.
3097 llvm::Type *IRTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty);

3099 llvm::Type *IRPtrTy = IRTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS);
3100 llvm::Value *Placeholder = llvm::UndefValue::get(IRPtrTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS));

3115void CodeGenFunction::EmitDelegateCallArg(CallArgList &args,
3116 const VarDecl *param,
3117 SourceLocation loc) {
3118 // StartFunction converted the ABI-lowered parameter(s) into a
3119 // local alloca. We need to turn that into an r-value suitable
3120 // for EmitCall.
3121 Address local = GetAddrOfLocalVar(param);
3122
3123 QualType type = param->getType();
3124
3125 if (isInAllocaArgument(CGM.getCXXABI(), type)) {
3126 CGM.ErrorUnsupported(param, "forwarded non-trivially copyable parameter");
3127 }
3128
3129 // GetAddrOfLocalVar returns a pointer-to-pointer for references,
3130 // but the argument needs to be the original pointer.
3131 if (type->isReferenceType()) {
3132 args.add(RValue::get(Builder.CreateLoad(local)), type);
3133
3134 // In ARC, move out of consumed arguments so that the release cleanup
3135 // entered by StartFunction doesn't cause an over-release. This isn't
3136 // optimal -O0 code generation, but it should get cleaned up when
3137 // optimization is enabled. This also assumes that delegate calls are
3138 // performed exactly once for a set of arguments, but that should be safe.
3139 } else if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
3140 param->hasAttr<NSConsumedAttr>() &&
3141 type->isObjCRetainableType()) {
3142 llvm::Value *ptr = Builder.CreateLoad(local);
3143 auto null =
3144 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(cast<llvm::PointerType>(ptr->getType()));
3145 Builder.CreateStore(null, local);
3146 args.add(RValue::get(ptr), type);
3147
3148 // For the most part, we just need to load the alloca, except that
3149 // aggregate r-values are actually pointers to temporaries.
3150 } else {
3151 args.add(convertTempToRValue(local, type, loc), type);
3152 }
3153
3154 // Deactivate the cleanup for the callee-destructed param that was pushed.
3155 if (hasAggregateEvaluationKind(type) && !CurFuncIsThunk &&
3156 type->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl()->isParamDestroyedInCallee() &&
3157 type.isDestructedType()) {
3158 EHScopeStack::stable_iterator cleanup =
3159 CalleeDestructedParamCleanups.lookup(cast<ParmVarDecl>(param));
3160 assert(cleanup.isValid() &&
3161 "cleanup for callee-destructed param not recorded");
3162 // This unreachable is a temporary marker which will be removed later.
3163 llvm::Instruction *isActive = Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3164 args.addArgCleanupDeactivation(cleanup, isActive);
3165 }
3166}

3168static bool isProvablyNull(llvm::Value *addr) {
3169 return isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(addr);
3170}

3172/// Emit the actual writing-back of a writeback.
3173static void emitWriteback(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3174 const CallArgList::Writeback &writeback) {
3175 const LValue &srcLV = writeback.Source;
3176 Address srcAddr = srcLV.getAddress();
3177 assert(!isProvablyNull(srcAddr.getPointer()) &&
3178 "shouldn't have writeback for provably null argument");
3179
3180 llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = nullptr;
3181
3182 // If the argument wasn't provably non-null, we need to null check
3183 // before doing the store.
3184 bool provablyNonNull = llvm::isKnownNonZero(srcAddr.getPointer(),
3185 CGF.CGM.getDataLayout());
3186 if (!provablyNonNull) {
3187 llvm::BasicBlock *writebackBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.writeback");
3188 contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.done");
3189
3190 llvm::Value *isNull =
3191 CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(srcAddr.getPointer(), "icr.isnull");
3192 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(isNull, contBB, writebackBB);
3193 CGF.EmitBlock(writebackBB);
3194 }
3195
3196 // Load the value to writeback.
3197 llvm::Value *value = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(writeback.Temporary);
3198
3199 // Cast it back, in case we're writing an id to a Foo* or something.
3200 value = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(value, srcAddr.getElementType(),
3201 "icr.writeback-cast");
3202
3203 // Perform the writeback.
3204
3205 // If we have a "to use" value, it's something we need to emit a use
3206 // of. This has to be carefully threaded in: if it's done after the
3207 // release it's potentially undefined behavior (and the optimizer
3208 // will ignore it), and if it happens before the retain then the
3209 // optimizer could move the release there.
3210 if (writeback.ToUse) {
3211 assert(srcLV.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong);
3212
3213 // Retain the new value. No need to block-copy here: the block's
3214 // being passed up the stack.
3215 value = CGF.EmitARCRetainNonBlock(value);
3216
3217 // Emit the intrinsic use here.
3218 CGF.EmitARCIntrinsicUse(writeback.ToUse);
3219
3220 // Load the old value (primitively).
3221 llvm::Value *oldValue = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(srcLV, SourceLocation());
3222
3223 // Put the new value in place (primitively).
3224 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(value, srcLV, /*init*/ false);
3225
3226 // Release the old value.
3227 CGF.EmitARCRelease(oldValue, srcLV.isARCPreciseLifetime());
3228
3229 // Otherwise, we can just do a normal lvalue store.
3230 } else {
3231 CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(value), srcLV);
3232 }
3233
3234 // Jump to the continuation block.
3235 if (!provablyNonNull)
3236 CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
3237}
3238
3239static void emitWritebacks(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3240 const CallArgList &args) {
3241 for (const auto &I : args.writebacks())
3242 emitWriteback(CGF, I);
3243}

3245static void deactivateArgCleanupsBeforeCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3246 const CallArgList &CallArgs) {
3247 ArrayRef<CallArgList::CallArgCleanup> Cleanups =
3248 CallArgs.getCleanupsToDeactivate();
3249 // Iterate in reverse to increase the likelihood of popping the cleanup.
3250 for (const auto &I : llvm::reverse(Cleanups)) {
3251 CGF.DeactivateCleanupBlock(I.Cleanup, I.IsActiveIP);
3252 I.IsActiveIP->eraseFromParent();
3253 }
3254}

3256static const Expr *maybeGetUnaryAddrOfOperand(const Expr *E) {
3257 if (const UnaryOperator *uop = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E->IgnoreParens()))
3258 if (uop->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
3259 return uop->getSubExpr();
3260 return nullptr;
3261}
3262
3263/// Emit an argument that's being passed call-by-writeback. That is,
3264/// we are passing the address of an __autoreleased temporary; it
3265/// might be copy-initialized with the current value of the given
3266/// address, but it will definitely be copied out of after the call.
3267static void emitWritebackArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, CallArgList &args,
3268 const ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr *CRE) {
3269 LValue srcLV;
3270
3271 // Make an optimistic effort to emit the address as an l-value.
3272 // This can fail if the argument expression is more complicated.
3273 if (const Expr *lvExpr = maybeGetUnaryAddrOfOperand(CRE->getSubExpr())) {
3274 srcLV = CGF.EmitLValue(lvExpr);
3275
3276 // Otherwise, just emit it as a scalar.
3277 } else {
3278 Address srcAddr = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(CRE->getSubExpr());
3279
3280 QualType srcAddrType =
3281 CRE->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
3282 srcLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(srcAddr, srcAddrType);
3283 }
3284 Address srcAddr = srcLV.getAddress();
3285
3286 // The dest and src types don't necessarily match in LLVM terms
3287 // because of the crazy ObjC compatibility rules.
3288
3289 llvm::PointerType *destType =
3290 cast<llvm::PointerType>(CGF.ConvertType(CRE->getType()));
3291
3292 // If the address is a constant null, just pass the appropriate null.
3293 if (isProvablyNull(srcAddr.getPointer())) {
3294 args.add(RValue::get(llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(destType)),
3295 CRE->getType());
3296 return;
3297 }
3298
3299 // Create the temporary.
3300 Address temp = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(destType->getElementType(),
3301 CGF.getPointerAlign(),
3302 "icr.temp");
3303 // Loading an l-value can introduce a cleanup if the l-value is __weak,
3304 // and that cleanup will be conditional if we can't prove that the l-value
3305 // isn't null, so we need to register a dominating point so that the cleanups
3306 // system will make valid IR.
3307 CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation condEval(CGF);
3308
3309 // Zero-initialize it if we're not doing a copy-initialization.
3310 bool shouldCopy = CRE->shouldCopy();
3311 if (!shouldCopy) {
3312 llvm::Value *null =
3313 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(
3314 cast<llvm::PointerType>(destType->getElementType()));
3315 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(null, temp);
3316 }
3317
3318 llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = nullptr;
3319 llvm::BasicBlock *originBB = nullptr;
3320
3321 // If the address is *not* known to be non-null, we need to switch.
3322 llvm::Value *finalArgument;
3323
3324 bool provablyNonNull = llvm::isKnownNonZero(srcAddr.getPointer(),
3325 CGF.CGM.getDataLayout());
3326 if (provablyNonNull) {
3327 finalArgument = temp.getPointer();
3328 } else {
3329 llvm::Value *isNull =
3330 CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(srcAddr.getPointer(), "icr.isnull");
3331
3332 finalArgument = CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(isNull,
3333 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(destType),
3334 temp.getPointer(), "icr.argument");
3335
3336 // If we need to copy, then the load has to be conditional, which
3337 // means we need control flow.
3338 if (shouldCopy) {
3339 originBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3340 contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.cont");
3341 llvm::BasicBlock *copyBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("icr.copy");
3342 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(isNull, contBB, copyBB);
3343 CGF.EmitBlock(copyBB);
3344 condEval.begin(CGF);
3345 }
3346 }
3347
3348 llvm::Value *valueToUse = nullptr;
3349
3350 // Perform a copy if necessary.
3351 if (shouldCopy) {
3352 RValue srcRV = CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(srcLV, SourceLocation());
3353 assert(srcRV.isScalar());
3354
3355 llvm::Value *src = srcRV.getScalarVal();
3356 src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, destType->getElementType(),
3357 "icr.cast");
3358
3359 // Use an ordinary store, not a store-to-lvalue.
3360 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(src, temp);
3361
3362 // If optimization is enabled, and the value was held in a
3363 // __strong variable, we need to tell the optimizer that this
3364 // value has to stay alive until we're doing the store back.
3365 // This is because the temporary is effectively unretained,
3366 // and so otherwise we can violate the high-level semantics.
3367 if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel != 0 &&
3368 srcLV.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong) {
3369 valueToUse = src;
3370 }
3371 }
3372
3373 // Finish the control flow if we needed it.
3374 if (shouldCopy && !provablyNonNull) {
3375 llvm::BasicBlock *copyBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3376 CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
3377
3378 // Make a phi for the value to intrinsically use.
3379 if (valueToUse) {
3380 llvm::PHINode *phiToUse = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(valueToUse->getType(), 2,
3381 "icr.to-use");
3382 phiToUse->addIncoming(valueToUse, copyBB);
3383 phiToUse->addIncoming(llvm::UndefValue::get(valueToUse->getType()),
3384 originBB);
3385 valueToUse = phiToUse;
3386 }
3387
3388 condEval.end(CGF);
3389 }
3390
3391 args.addWriteback(srcLV, temp, valueToUse);
3392 args.add(RValue::get(finalArgument), CRE->getType());
3393}

3413void CodeGenFunction::EmitNonNullArgCheck(RValue RV, QualType ArgType,
3414 SourceLocation ArgLoc,
3415 AbstractCallee AC,
3416 unsigned ParmNum) {
3417 if (!AC.getDecl() || !(SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NonnullAttribute) ||
3418 SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NullabilityArg)))
3419 return;
3420
3421 // The param decl may be missing in a variadic function.
3422 auto PVD = ParmNum < AC.getNumParams() ? AC.getParamDecl(ParmNum) : nullptr;
3423 unsigned ArgNo = PVD ? PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex() : ParmNum;
3424
3425 // Prefer the nonnull attribute if it's present.
3426 const NonNullAttr *NNAttr = nullptr;
3427 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NonnullAttribute))
3428 NNAttr = getNonNullAttr(AC.getDecl(), PVD, ArgType, ArgNo);
3429
3430 bool CanCheckNullability = false;
3431 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::NullabilityArg) && !NNAttr && PVD) {
3432 auto Nullability = PVD->getType()->getNullability(getContext());
3433 CanCheckNullability = Nullability &&
3434 *Nullability == NullabilityKind::NonNull &&
3435 PVD->getTypeSourceInfo();
3436 }
3437
3438 if (!NNAttr && !CanCheckNullability)
3439 return;
3440
3441 SourceLocation AttrLoc;
3442 SanitizerMask CheckKind;
3443 SanitizerHandler Handler;
3444 if (NNAttr) {
3445 AttrLoc = NNAttr->getLocation();
3446 CheckKind = SanitizerKind::NonnullAttribute;
3447 Handler = SanitizerHandler::NonnullArg;
3448 } else {
3449 AttrLoc = PVD->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc().findNullabilityLoc();
3450 CheckKind = SanitizerKind::NullabilityArg;
3451 Handler = SanitizerHandler::NullabilityArg;
3452 }
3453
3454 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
3455 assert(RV.isScalar());
3456 llvm::Value *V = RV.getScalarVal();
3457 llvm::Value *Cond =
3458 Builder.CreateICmpNE(V, llvm::Constant::getNullValue(V->getType()));
3459 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
3460 EmitCheckSourceLocation(ArgLoc), EmitCheckSourceLocation(AttrLoc),
3461 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, ArgNo + 1),
3462 };
3463 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Cond, CheckKind), Handler, StaticData, None);
3464}
3465
3466void CodeGenFunction::EmitCallArgs(
3467 CallArgList &Args, ArrayRef<QualType> ArgTypes,
3468 llvm::iterator_range<CallExpr::const_arg_iterator> ArgRange,
3469 AbstractCallee AC, unsigned ParamsToSkip, EvaluationOrder Order) {
3470 assert((int)ArgTypes.size() == (ArgRange.end() - ArgRange.begin()));
3471
3472 // We *have* to evaluate arguments from right to left in the MS C++ ABI,
3473 // because arguments are destroyed left to right in the callee. As a special
3474 // case, there are certain language constructs that require left-to-right
3475 // evaluation, and in those cases we consider the evaluation order requirement
3476 // to trump the "destruction order is reverse construction order" guarantee.
3477 bool LeftToRight =
3478 CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().areArgsDestroyedLeftToRightInCallee()
3479 ? Order == EvaluationOrder::ForceLeftToRight
3480 : Order != EvaluationOrder::ForceRightToLeft;
3481
3482 auto MaybeEmitImplicitObjectSize = [&](unsigned I, const Expr *Arg,
3483 RValue EmittedArg) {
3484 if (!AC.hasFunctionDecl() || I >= AC.getNumParams())
3485 return;
3486 auto *PS = AC.getParamDecl(I)->getAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>();
3487 if (PS == nullptr)
3488 return;
3489
3490 const auto &Context = getContext();
3491 auto SizeTy = Context.getSizeType();
3492 auto T = Builder.getIntNTy(Context.getTypeSize(SizeTy));
3493 assert(EmittedArg.getScalarVal() && "We emitted nothing for the arg?");
3494 llvm::Value *V = evaluateOrEmitBuiltinObjectSize(Arg, PS->getType(), T,
3495 EmittedArg.getScalarVal(),
3496 PS->isDynamic());
3497 Args.add(RValue::get(V), SizeTy);
3498 // If we're emitting args in reverse, be sure to do so with
3499 // pass_object_size, as well.
3500 if (!LeftToRight)
3501 std::swap(Args.back(), *(&Args.back() - 1));
3502 };
3503
3504 // Insert a stack save if we're going to need any inalloca args.
3505 bool HasInAllocaArgs = false;
3506 if (CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
3507 for (ArrayRef<QualType>::iterator I = ArgTypes.begin(), E = ArgTypes.end();
3508 I != E && !HasInAllocaArgs; ++I)
3509 HasInAllocaArgs = isInAllocaArgument(CGM.getCXXABI(), *I);
3510 if (HasInAllocaArgs) {
3511 assert(getTarget().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86);
3512 Args.allocateArgumentMemory(*this);
3513 }
3514 }
3515
3516 // Evaluate each argument in the appropriate order.
3517 size_t CallArgsStart = Args.size();
3518 for (unsigned I = 0, E = ArgTypes.size(); I != E; ++I) {
3519 unsigned Idx = LeftToRight ? I : E - I - 1;
3520 CallExpr::const_arg_iterator Arg = ArgRange.begin() + Idx;
3521 unsigned InitialArgSize = Args.size();
3522 // If *Arg is an ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr, check that either the types of
3523 // the argument and parameter match or the objc method is parameterized.
3524 assert((!isa<ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr>(*Arg) ||
3525 getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType((*Arg)->getType(),
3526 ArgTypes[Idx]) ||
3527 (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(AC.getDecl()) &&
3528 isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(AC.getDecl())))) &&
3529 "Argument and parameter types don't match");
3530 EmitCallArg(Args, *Arg, ArgTypes[Idx]);
3531 // In particular, we depend on it being the last arg in Args, and the
3532 // objectsize bits depend on there only being one arg if !LeftToRight.
3533 assert(InitialArgSize + 1 == Args.size() &&
3534 "The code below depends on only adding one arg per EmitCallArg");
3535 (void)InitialArgSize;
3536 // Since pointer argument are never emitted as LValue, it is safe to emit
3537 // non-null argument check for r-value only.
3538 if (!Args.back().hasLValue()) {
3539 RValue RVArg = Args.back().getKnownRValue();
3540 EmitNonNullArgCheck(RVArg, ArgTypes[Idx], (*Arg)->getExprLoc(), AC,
3541 ParamsToSkip + Idx);
3542 // @llvm.objectsize should never have side-effects and shouldn't need
3543 // destruction/cleanups, so we can safely "emit" it after its arg,
3544 // regardless of right-to-leftness
3545 MaybeEmitImplicitObjectSize(Idx, *Arg, RVArg);
3546 }
3547 }
3548
3549 if (!LeftToRight) {
3550 // Un-reverse the arguments we just evaluated so they match up with the LLVM
3551 // IR function.
3552 std::reverse(Args.begin() + CallArgsStart, Args.end());
3553 }
3554}
3555
3556namespace {
3557
3558struct DestroyUnpassedArg final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
3559 DestroyUnpassedArg(Address Addr, QualType Ty)
3560 : Addr(Addr), Ty(Ty) {}
3561
3562 Address Addr;
3563 QualType Ty;
3564
3565 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
3566 QualType::DestructionKind DtorKind = Ty.isDestructedType();
3567 if (DtorKind == QualType::DK_cxx_destructor) {
3568 const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl()->getDestructor();
3569 assert(!Dtor->isTrivial());
3570 CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(Dtor, Dtor_Complete, /*for vbase*/ false,
3571 /*Delegating=*/false, Addr);
3572 } else {
3573 CGF.callCStructDestructor(CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, Ty));
3574 }
3575 }
3576};

3578struct DisableDebugLocationUpdates {
3579 CodeGenFunction &CGF;
3580 bool disabledDebugInfo;
3581 DisableDebugLocationUpdates(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E) : CGF(CGF) {
3582 if ((disabledDebugInfo = isa<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(E) && CGF.getDebugInfo()))
3583 CGF.disableDebugInfo();
3584 }
3585 ~DisableDebugLocationUpdates() {
3586 if (disabledDebugInfo)
3587 CGF.enableDebugInfo();
3588 }
3589};

3593RValue CallArg::getRValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
3594 if (!HasLV)
3595 return RV;
3596 LValue Copy = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(CGF.CreateMemTemp(Ty), Ty);
3597 CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(Copy, LV, Ty, AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap,
3598 LV.isVolatile());
3599 IsUsed = true;
3600 return RValue::getAggregate(Copy.getAddress());
3601}
3602
3603void CallArg::copyInto(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address Addr) const {
3604 LValue Dst = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, Ty);
3605 if (!HasLV && RV.isScalar())
3606 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(RV.getScalarVal(), Dst, /*init=*/true);
3607 else if (!HasLV && RV.isComplex())
3608 CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex(RV.getComplexVal(), Dst, /*init=*/true);
3609 else {
3610 auto Addr = HasLV ? LV.getAddress() : RV.getAggregateAddress();
3611 LValue SrcLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, Ty);
3612 // We assume that call args are never copied into subobjects.
3613 CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(Dst, SrcLV, Ty, AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap,
3614 HasLV ? LV.isVolatileQualified()
3615 : RV.isVolatileQualified());
3616 }
3617 IsUsed = true;
3618}
3619
3620void CodeGenFunction::EmitCallArg(CallArgList &args, const Expr *E,
3621 QualType type) {
3622 DisableDebugLocationUpdates Dis(*this, E);
3623 if (const ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr *CRE
3624 = dyn_cast<ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr>(E)) {
3625 assert(getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount);
3626 return emitWritebackArg(*this, args, CRE);
3627 }
3628
3629 assert(type->isReferenceType() == E->isGLValue() &&
3630 "reference binding to unmaterialized r-value!");
3631
3632 if (E->isGLValue()) {
3633 assert(E->getObjectKind() == OK_Ordinary);
3634 return args.add(EmitReferenceBindingToExpr(E), type);
3635 }
3636
3637 bool HasAggregateEvalKind = hasAggregateEvaluationKind(type);
3638
3639 // In the Microsoft C++ ABI, aggregate arguments are destructed by the callee.
3640 // However, we still have to push an EH-only cleanup in case we unwind before
3641 // we make it to the call.
3642 if (HasAggregateEvalKind &&
3643 type->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl()->isParamDestroyedInCallee()) {
3644 // If we're using inalloca, use the argument memory. Otherwise, use a
3645 // temporary.
3646 AggValueSlot Slot;
3647 if (args.isUsingInAlloca())
3648 Slot = createPlaceholderSlot(*this, type);
3649 else
3650 Slot = CreateAggTemp(type, "agg.tmp");
3651
3652 bool DestroyedInCallee = true, NeedsEHCleanup = true;
3653 if (const auto *RD = type->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
3654 DestroyedInCallee = RD->hasNonTrivialDestructor();
3655 else
3656 NeedsEHCleanup = needsEHCleanup(type.isDestructedType());
3657
3658 if (DestroyedInCallee)
3659 Slot.setExternallyDestructed();
3660
3661 EmitAggExpr(E, Slot);
3662 RValue RV = Slot.asRValue();
3663 args.add(RV, type);
3664
3665 if (DestroyedInCallee && NeedsEHCleanup) {
3666 // Create a no-op GEP between the placeholder and the cleanup so we can
3667 // RAUW it successfully. It also serves as a marker of the first
3668 // instruction where the cleanup is active.
3669 pushFullExprCleanup<DestroyUnpassedArg>(EHCleanup, Slot.getAddress(),
3670 type);
3671 // This unreachable is a temporary marker which will be removed later.
3672 llvm::Instruction *IsActive = Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3673 args.addArgCleanupDeactivation(EHStack.getInnermostEHScope(), IsActive);
3674 }
3675 return;
3676 }
3677
3678 if (HasAggregateEvalKind && isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(E) &&
3679 cast<CastExpr>(E)->getCastKind() == CK_LValueToRValue) {
3680 LValue L = EmitLValue(cast<CastExpr>(E)->getSubExpr());
3681 assert(L.isSimple());
3682 args.addUncopiedAggregate(L, type);
3683 return;
3684 }
3685
3686 args.add(EmitAnyExprToTemp(E), type);
3687}

3689QualType CodeGenFunction::getVarArgType(const Expr *Arg) {
3690 // System headers on Windows define NULL to 0 instead of 0LL on Win64. MSVC
3691 // implicitly widens null pointer constants that are arguments to varargs
3692 // functions to pointer-sized ints.
3693 if (!getTarget().getTriple().isOSWindows())
3694 return Arg->getType();
3695
3696 if (Arg->getType()->isIntegerType() &&
3697 getContext().getTypeSize(Arg->getType()) <
3698 getContext().getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0) &&
3699 Arg->isNullPointerConstant(getContext(),
3700 Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull)) {
3701 return getContext().getIntPtrType();
3702 }
3703
3704 return Arg->getType();
3705}

3741// Calls which may throw must have operand bundles indicating which funclet
3742// they are nested within.
3743SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1>
3744CodeGenFunction::getBundlesForFunclet(llvm::Value *Callee) {
3745 SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList;
3746 // There is no need for a funclet operand bundle if we aren't inside a
3747 // funclet.
3748 if (!CurrentFuncletPad)
3749 return BundleList;
3750
3751 // Skip intrinsics which cannot throw.
3752 auto *CalleeFn = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Callee->stripPointerCasts());
3753 if (CalleeFn && CalleeFn->isIntrinsic() && CalleeFn->doesNotThrow())
3754 return BundleList;
3755
3756 BundleList.emplace_back("funclet", CurrentFuncletPad);
3757 return BundleList;
3758}

3770/// Emits a call or invoke to the given noreturn runtime function.
3771void CodeGenFunction::EmitNoreturnRuntimeCallOrInvoke(
3772 llvm::FunctionCallee callee, ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> args) {
3773 SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList =
3774 getBundlesForFunclet(callee.getCallee());
3775
3776 if (getInvokeDest()) {
3777 llvm::InvokeInst *invoke =
3778 Builder.CreateInvoke(callee,
3779 getUnreachableBlock(),
3780 getInvokeDest(),
3781 args,
3782 BundleList);
3783 invoke->setDoesNotReturn();
3784 invoke->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
3785 } else {
3786 llvm::CallInst *call = Builder.CreateCall(callee, args, BundleList);
3787 call->setDoesNotReturn();
3788 call->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
3789 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3790 }
3791}

3810/// Emits a call or invoke instruction to the given function, depending
3811/// on the current state of the EH stack.
3812llvm::CallBase *CodeGenFunction::EmitCallOrInvoke(llvm::FunctionCallee Callee,
3813 ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> Args,
3814 const Twine &Name) {
3815 llvm::BasicBlock *InvokeDest = getInvokeDest();
3816 SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList =
3817 getBundlesForFunclet(Callee.getCallee());
3818
3819 llvm::CallBase *Inst;
3820 if (!InvokeDest)
3821 Inst = Builder.CreateCall(Callee, Args, BundleList, Name);
3822 else {
3823 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB = createBasicBlock("invoke.cont");
3824 Inst = Builder.CreateInvoke(Callee, ContBB, InvokeDest, Args, BundleList,
3825 Name);
3826 EmitBlock(ContBB);
3827 }
3828
3829 // In ObjC ARC mode with no ObjC ARC exception safety, tell the ARC
3830 // optimizer it can aggressively ignore unwind edges.
3831 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
3832 AddObjCARCExceptionMetadata(Inst);
3833
3834 return Inst;
3835}
