3838 llvm::Value *New) {
3839 DeferredReplacements.push_back(std::make_pair(Old, New));
3840}
3841
3842RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCall(const CGFunctionInfo &CallInfo,
3843 const CGCallee &Callee,
3844 ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
3845 const CallArgList &CallArgs,
3846 llvm::CallBase **callOrInvoke,
3847 SourceLocation Loc) {
3848 // FIXME: We no longer need the types from CallArgs; lift up and simplify.
3849
3850 assert(Callee.isOrdinary() || Callee.isVirtual());
3851
3852 // Handle struct-return functions by passing a pointer to the
3853 // location that we would like to return into.
3854 QualType RetTy = CallInfo.getReturnType();
3855 const ABIArgInfo &RetAI = CallInfo.getReturnInfo();
3856
3857 llvm::FunctionType *IRFuncTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(CallInfo);
3858
3859 const Decl *TargetDecl = Callee.getAbstractInfo().getCalleeDecl().getDecl();
3860
3861#ifndef NDEBUG
3862 if (!(CallInfo.isVariadic() && CallInfo.getArgStruct())) {
3863 // For an inalloca varargs function, we don't expect CallInfo to match the
3864 // function pointer's type, because the inalloca struct a will have extra
3865 // fields in it for the varargs parameters. Code later in this function
3866 // bitcasts the function pointer to the type derived from CallInfo.
3867 //
3868 // In other cases, we assert that the types match up (until pointers stop
3869 // having pointee types).
3870 llvm::Type *TypeFromVal;
3871 if (Callee.isVirtual())
3872 TypeFromVal = Callee.getVirtualFunctionType();
3873 else
3874 TypeFromVal =
3875 Callee.getFunctionPointer()->getType()->getPointerElementType();
3876 assert(IRFuncTy == TypeFromVal);
3877 }
3878#endif
3879
3880 // 1. Set up the arguments.
3881
3882 // If we're using inalloca, insert the allocation after the stack save.
3883 // FIXME: Do this earlier rather than hacking it in here!
3884 Address ArgMemory = Address::invalid();
3885 if (llvm::StructType *ArgStruct = CallInfo.getArgStruct()) {
3886 const llvm::DataLayout &DL = CGM.getDataLayout();
3887 llvm::Instruction *IP = CallArgs.getStackBase();
3888 llvm::AllocaInst *AI;
3889 if (IP) {
3890 IP = IP->getNextNode();
3891 AI = new llvm::AllocaInst(ArgStruct, DL.getAllocaAddrSpace(),
3892 "argmem", IP);
3893 } else {
3894 AI = CreateTempAlloca(ArgStruct, "argmem");
3895 }
3896 auto Align = CallInfo.getArgStructAlignment();
3897 AI->setAlignment(Align.getQuantity());
3898 AI->setUsedWithInAlloca(true);
3899 assert(AI->isUsedWithInAlloca() && !AI->isStaticAlloca());
3900 ArgMemory = Address(AI, Align);
3901 }
3902
3903 ClangToLLVMArgMapping IRFunctionArgs(CGM.getContext(), CallInfo);
3904 SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 16> IRCallArgs(IRFunctionArgs.totalIRArgs());
3905
3906 // If the call returns a temporary with struct return, create a temporary
3907 // alloca to hold the result, unless one is given to us.
3908 Address SRetPtr = Address::invalid();
3909 Address SRetAlloca = Address::invalid();
3910 llvm::Value *UnusedReturnSizePtr = nullptr;
3911 if (RetAI.isIndirect() || RetAI.isInAlloca() || RetAI.isCoerceAndExpand()) {
3912 if (!ReturnValue.isNull()) {
3913 SRetPtr = ReturnValue.getValue();
3914 } else {
3915 SRetPtr = CreateMemTemp(RetTy, "tmp", &SRetAlloca);
3916 if (HaveInsertPoint() && ReturnValue.isUnused()) {
3917 uint64_t size =
3918 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ConvertTypeForMem(RetTy));
3919 UnusedReturnSizePtr = EmitLifetimeStart(size, SRetAlloca.getPointer());
3920 }
3921 }
3922 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasSRetArg()) {
3923 IRCallArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getSRetArgNo()] = SRetPtr.getPointer();
3924 } else if (RetAI.isInAlloca()) {
3925 Address Addr =
3926 Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory, RetAI.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
3927 Builder.CreateStore(SRetPtr.getPointer(), Addr);
3928 }
3929 }
3930
3931 Address swiftErrorTemp = Address::invalid();
3932 Address swiftErrorArg = Address::invalid();
3933
3934 // Translate all of the arguments as necessary to match the IR lowering.
3935 assert(CallInfo.arg_size() == CallArgs.size() &&
3936 "Mismatch between function signature & arguments.");
3937 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
3938 CGFunctionInfo::const_arg_iterator info_it = CallInfo.arg_begin();
3939 for (CallArgList::const_iterator I = CallArgs.begin(), E = CallArgs.end();
3940 I != E; ++I, ++info_it, ++ArgNo) {
3941 const ABIArgInfo &ArgInfo = info_it->info;
3942
3943 // Insert a padding argument to ensure proper alignment.
3944 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasPaddingArg(ArgNo))
3945 IRCallArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getPaddingArgNo(ArgNo)] =
3946 llvm::UndefValue::get(ArgInfo.getPaddingType());
3947
3948 unsigned FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs;
3949 std::tie(FirstIRArg, NumIRArgs) = IRFunctionArgs.getIRArgs(ArgNo);
3950
3951 switch (ArgInfo.getKind()) {
3952 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca: {
3953 assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
3954 assert(getTarget().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86);
3955 if (I->isAggregate()) {
3956 // Replace the placeholder with the appropriate argument slot GEP.
3957 Address Addr = I->hasLValue()
3958 ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress()
3959 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
3960 llvm::Instruction *Placeholder =
3961 cast<llvm::Instruction>(Addr.getPointer());
3962 CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint IP = Builder.saveIP();
3963 Builder.SetInsertPoint(Placeholder);
3964 Addr =
3965 Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory, ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
3966 Builder.restoreIP(IP);
3967 deferPlaceholderReplacement(Placeholder, Addr.getPointer());
3968 } else {
3969 // Store the RValue into the argument struct.
3970 Address Addr =
3971 Builder.CreateStructGEP(ArgMemory, ArgInfo.getInAllocaFieldIndex());
3972 unsigned AS = Addr.getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
3973 llvm::Type *MemType = ConvertTypeForMem(I->Ty)->getPointerTo(AS);
3974 // There are some cases where a trivial bitcast is not avoidable. The
3975 // definition of a type later in a translation unit may change it's type
3976 // from {}* to (%struct.foo*)*.
3977 if (Addr.getType() != MemType)
3978 Addr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Addr, MemType);
3979 I->copyInto(*this, Addr);
3980 }
3981 break;
3982 }
3983
3984 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
3985 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
3986 if (!I->isAggregate()) {
3987 // Make a temporary alloca to pass the argument.
3988 Address Addr = CreateMemTempWithoutCast(
3989 I->Ty, ArgInfo.getIndirectAlign(), "indirect-arg-temp");
3990 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = Addr.getPointer();
3991
3992 I->copyInto(*this, Addr);
3993 } else {
3994 // We want to avoid creating an unnecessary temporary+copy here;
3995 // however, we need one in three cases:
3996 // 1. If the argument is not byval, and we are required to copy the
3997 // source. (This case doesn't occur on any common architecture.)
3998 // 2. If the argument is byval, RV is not sufficiently aligned, and
3999 // we cannot force it to be sufficiently aligned.
4000 // 3. If the argument is byval, but RV is not located in default
4001 // or alloca address space.
4002 Address Addr = I->hasLValue()
4003 ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress()
4004 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
4005 llvm::Value *V = Addr.getPointer();
4006 CharUnits Align = ArgInfo.getIndirectAlign();
4007 const llvm::DataLayout *TD = &CGM.getDataLayout();
4008
4009 assert((FirstIRArg >= IRFuncTy->getNumParams() ||
4010 IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg)->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
4011 TD->getAllocaAddrSpace()) &&
4012 "indirect argument must be in alloca address space");
4013
4014 bool NeedCopy = false;
4015
4016 if (Addr.getAlignment() < Align &&
4017 llvm::getOrEnforceKnownAlignment(V, Align.getQuantity(), *TD) <
4018 Align.getQuantity()) {
4019 NeedCopy = true;
4020 } else if (I->hasLValue()) {
4021 auto LV = I->getKnownLValue();
4022 auto AS = LV.getAddressSpace();
4023
4024 if ((!ArgInfo.getIndirectByVal() &&
4025 (LV.getAlignment() >=
4026 getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(I->Ty)))) {
4027 NeedCopy = true;
4028 }
4029 if (!getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
4030 if ((ArgInfo.getIndirectByVal() &&
4031 (AS != LangAS::Default &&
4032 AS != CGM.getASTAllocaAddressSpace()))) {
4033 NeedCopy = true;
4034 }
4035 }
4036 // For OpenCL even if RV is located in default or alloca address space
4037 // we don't want to perform address space cast for it.
4038 else if ((ArgInfo.getIndirectByVal() &&
4039 Addr.getType()->getAddressSpace() != IRFuncTy->
4040 getParamType(FirstIRArg)->getPointerAddressSpace())) {
4041 NeedCopy = true;
4042 }
4043 }
4044
4045 if (NeedCopy) {
4046 // Create an aligned temporary, and copy to it.
4047 Address AI = CreateMemTempWithoutCast(
4048 I->Ty, ArgInfo.getIndirectAlign(), "byval-temp");
4049 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = AI.getPointer();
4050 I->copyInto(*this, AI);
4051 } else {
4052 // Skip the extra memcpy call.
4053 auto *T = V->getType()->getPointerElementType()->getPointerTo(
4054 CGM.getDataLayout().getAllocaAddrSpace());
4055 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
4056 *this, V, LangAS::Default, CGM.getASTAllocaAddressSpace(), T,
4057 true);
4058 }
4059 }
4060 break;
4061 }
4062
4063 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
4064 assert(NumIRArgs == 0);
4065 break;
4066
4067 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
4068 case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
4069 if (!isa<llvm::StructType>(ArgInfo.getCoerceToType()) &&
4070 ArgInfo.getCoerceToType() == ConvertType(info_it->type) &&
4071 ArgInfo.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
4072 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
4073 llvm::Value *V;
4074 if (!I->isAggregate())
4075 V = I->getKnownRValue().getScalarVal();
4076 else
4077 V = Builder.CreateLoad(
4078 I->hasLValue() ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress()
4079 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress());
4080
4081 // Implement swifterror by copying into a new swifterror argument.
4082 // We'll write back in the normal path out of the call.
4083 if (CallInfo.getExtParameterInfo(ArgNo).getABI()
4084 == ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult) {
4085 assert(!swiftErrorTemp.isValid() && "multiple swifterror args");
4086
4087 QualType pointeeTy = I->Ty->getPointeeType();
4088 swiftErrorArg =
4089 Address(V, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(pointeeTy));
4090
4091 swiftErrorTemp =
4092 CreateMemTemp(pointeeTy, getPointerAlign(), "swifterror.temp");
4093 V = swiftErrorTemp.getPointer();
4094 cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(V)->setSwiftError(true);
4095
4096 llvm::Value *errorValue = Builder.CreateLoad(swiftErrorArg);
4097 Builder.CreateStore(errorValue, swiftErrorTemp);
4098 }
4099
4100 // We might have to widen integers, but we should never truncate.
4101 if (ArgInfo.getCoerceToType() != V->getType() &&
4102 V->getType()->isIntegerTy())
4103 V = Builder.CreateZExt(V, ArgInfo.getCoerceToType());
4104
4105 // If the argument doesn't match, perform a bitcast to coerce it. This
4106 // can happen due to trivial type mismatches.
4107 if (FirstIRArg < IRFuncTy->getNumParams() &&
4108 V->getType() != IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg))
4109 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, IRFuncTy->getParamType(FirstIRArg));
4110
4111 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] = V;
4112 break;
4113 }
4114
4115 // FIXME: Avoid the conversion through memory if possible.
4116 Address Src = Address::invalid();
4117 if (!I->isAggregate()) {
4118 Src = CreateMemTemp(I->Ty, "coerce");
4119 I->copyInto(*this, Src);
4120 } else {
4121 Src = I->hasLValue() ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress()
4122 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
4123 }
4124
4125 // If the value is offset in memory, apply the offset now.
4126 Src = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, Src, ArgInfo);
4127
4128 // Fast-isel and the optimizer generally like scalar values better than
4129 // FCAs, so we flatten them if this is safe to do for this argument.
4130 llvm::StructType *STy =
4131 dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(ArgInfo.getCoerceToType());
4132 if (STy && ArgInfo.isDirect() && ArgInfo.getCanBeFlattened()) {
4133 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src.getType()->getElementType();
4134 uint64_t SrcSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
4135 uint64_t DstSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(STy);
4136
4137 // If the source type is smaller than the destination type of the
4138 // coerce-to logic, copy the source value into a temp alloca the size
4139 // of the destination type to allow loading all of it. The bits past
4140 // the source value are left undef.
4141 if (SrcSize < DstSize) {
4142 Address TempAlloca
4143 = CreateTempAlloca(STy, Src.getAlignment(),
4144 Src.getName() + ".coerce");
4145 Builder.CreateMemCpy(TempAlloca, Src, SrcSize);
4146 Src = TempAlloca;
4147 } else {
4148 Src = Builder.CreateBitCast(Src,
4149 STy->getPointerTo(Src.getAddressSpace()));
4150 }
4151
4152 assert(NumIRArgs == STy->getNumElements());
4153 for (unsigned i = 0, e = STy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
4154 Address EltPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(Src, i);
4155 llvm::Value *LI = Builder.CreateLoad(EltPtr);
4156 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg + i] = LI;
4157 }
4158 } else {
4159 // In the simple case, just pass the coerced loaded value.
4160 assert(NumIRArgs == 1);
4161 IRCallArgs[FirstIRArg] =
4162 CreateCoercedLoad(Src, ArgInfo.getCoerceToType(), *this);
4163 }
4164
4165 break;
4166 }
4167
4168 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
4169 auto coercionType = ArgInfo.getCoerceAndExpandType();
4170 auto layout = CGM.getDataLayout().getStructLayout(coercionType);
4171
4172 llvm::Value *tempSize = nullptr;
4173 Address addr = Address::invalid();
4174 Address AllocaAddr = Address::invalid();
4175 if (I->isAggregate()) {
4176 addr = I->hasLValue() ? I->getKnownLValue().getAddress()
4177 : I->getKnownRValue().getAggregateAddress();
4178
4179 } else {
4180 RValue RV = I->getKnownRValue();
4181 assert(RV.isScalar()); // complex should always just be direct
4182
4183 llvm::Type *scalarType = RV.getScalarVal()->getType();
4184 auto scalarSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(scalarType);
4185 auto scalarAlign = CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlignment(scalarType);
4186
4187 // Materialize to a temporary.
4188 addr = CreateTempAlloca(RV.getScalarVal()->getType(),
4189 CharUnits::fromQuantity(std::max(
4190 layout->getAlignment(), scalarAlign)),
4191 "tmp",
4192 /*ArraySize=*/nullptr, &AllocaAddr);
4193 tempSize = EmitLifetimeStart(scalarSize, AllocaAddr.getPointer());
4194
4195 Builder.CreateStore(RV.getScalarVal(), addr);
4196 }
4197
4198 addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(addr, coercionType);
4199
4200 unsigned IRArgPos = FirstIRArg;
4201 for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
4202 llvm::Type *eltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
4203 if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(eltType)) continue;
4204 Address eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, i);
4205 llvm::Value *elt = Builder.CreateLoad(eltAddr);
4206 IRCallArgs[IRArgPos++] = elt;
4207 }
4208 assert(IRArgPos == FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
4209
4210 if (tempSize) {
4211 EmitLifetimeEnd(tempSize, AllocaAddr.getPointer());
4212 }
4213
4214 break;
4215 }
4216
4217 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
4218 unsigned IRArgPos = FirstIRArg;
4219 ExpandTypeToArgs(I->Ty, *I, IRFuncTy, IRCallArgs, IRArgPos);
4220 assert(IRArgPos == FirstIRArg + NumIRArgs);
4221 break;
4222 }
4223 }
4224
4225 const CGCallee &ConcreteCallee = Callee.prepareConcreteCallee(*this);
4226 llvm::Value *CalleePtr = ConcreteCallee.getFunctionPointer();
4227
4228 // If we're using inalloca, set up that argument.
4229 if (ArgMemory.isValid()) {
4230 llvm::Value *Arg = ArgMemory.getPointer();
4231 if (CallInfo.isVariadic()) {
4232 // When passing non-POD arguments by value to variadic functions, we will
4233 // end up with a variadic prototype and an inalloca call site. In such
4234 // cases, we can't do any parameter mismatch checks. Give up and bitcast
4235 // the callee.
4236 unsigned CalleeAS = CalleePtr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
4237 CalleePtr =
4238 Builder.CreateBitCast(CalleePtr, IRFuncTy->getPointerTo(CalleeAS));
4239 } else {
4240 llvm::Type *LastParamTy =
4241 IRFuncTy->getParamType(IRFuncTy->getNumParams() - 1);
4242 if (Arg->getType() != LastParamTy) {
4243#ifndef NDEBUG
4244 // Assert that these structs have equivalent element types.
4245 llvm::StructType *FullTy = CallInfo.getArgStruct();
4246 llvm::StructType *DeclaredTy = cast<llvm::StructType>(
4247 cast<llvm::PointerType>(LastParamTy)->getElementType());
4248 assert(DeclaredTy->getNumElements() == FullTy->getNumElements());
4249 for (llvm::StructType::element_iterator DI = DeclaredTy->element_begin(),
4250 DE = DeclaredTy->element_end(),
4251 FI = FullTy->element_begin();
4252 DI != DE; ++DI, ++FI)
4253 assert(*DI == *FI);
4254#endif
4255 Arg = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg, LastParamTy);
4256 }
4257 }
4258 assert(IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg());
4259 IRCallArgs[IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo()] = Arg;
4260 }
4261
4262 // 2. Prepare the function pointer.
4263
4264 // If the callee is a bitcast of a non-variadic function to have a
4265 // variadic function pointer type, check to see if we can remove the
4266 // bitcast. This comes up with unprototyped functions.
4267 //
4268 // This makes the IR nicer, but more importantly it ensures that we
4269 // can inline the function at -O0 if it is marked always_inline.
4270 auto simplifyVariadicCallee = [](llvm::FunctionType *CalleeFT,
4271 llvm::Value *Ptr) -> llvm::Function * {
4272 if (!CalleeFT->isVarArg())
4273 return nullptr;
4274
4275 // Get underlying value if it's a bitcast
4276 if (llvm::ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(Ptr)) {
4277 if (CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::BitCast)
4278 Ptr = CE->getOperand(0);
4279 }
4280
4281 llvm::Function *OrigFn = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Ptr);
4282 if (!OrigFn)
4283 return nullptr;
4284
4285 llvm::FunctionType *OrigFT = OrigFn->getFunctionType();
4286
4287 // If the original type is variadic, or if any of the component types
4288 // disagree, we cannot remove the cast.
4289 if (OrigFT->isVarArg() ||
4290 OrigFT->getNumParams() != CalleeFT->getNumParams() ||
4291 OrigFT->getReturnType() != CalleeFT->getReturnType())
4292 return nullptr;
4293
4294 for (unsigned i = 0, e = OrigFT->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i)
4295 if (OrigFT->getParamType(i) != CalleeFT->getParamType(i))
4296 return nullptr;
4297
4298 return OrigFn;
4299 };
4300
4301 if (llvm::Function *OrigFn = simplifyVariadicCallee(IRFuncTy, CalleePtr)) {
4302 CalleePtr = OrigFn;
4303 IRFuncTy = OrigFn->getFunctionType();
4304 }
4305
4306 // 3. Perform the actual call.
4307
4308 // Deactivate any cleanups that we're supposed to do immediately before
4309 // the call.
4310 if (!CallArgs.getCleanupsToDeactivate().empty())
4311 deactivateArgCleanupsBeforeCall(*this, CallArgs);
4312
4313 // Assert that the arguments we computed match up. The IR verifier
4314 // will catch this, but this is a common enough source of problems
4315 // during IRGen changes that it's way better for debugging to catch
4316 // it ourselves here.
4317#ifndef NDEBUG
4318 assert(IRCallArgs.size() == IRFuncTy->getNumParams() || IRFuncTy->isVarArg());
4319 for (unsigned i = 0; i < IRCallArgs.size(); ++i) {
4320 // Inalloca argument can have different type.
4321 if (IRFunctionArgs.hasInallocaArg() &&
4322 i == IRFunctionArgs.getInallocaArgNo())
4323 continue;
4324 if (i < IRFuncTy->getNumParams())
4325 assert(IRCallArgs[i]->getType() == IRFuncTy->getParamType(i));
4326 }
4327#endif
4328
4329 // Update the largest vector width if any arguments have vector types.
4330 for (unsigned i = 0; i < IRCallArgs.size(); ++i) {
4331 if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(IRCallArgs[i]->getType()))
4332 LargestVectorWidth = std::max(LargestVectorWidth,
4333 VT->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
4334 }
4335
4336 // Compute the calling convention and attributes.
4337 unsigned CallingConv;
4338 llvm::AttributeList Attrs;
4339 CGM.ConstructAttributeList(CalleePtr->getName(), CallInfo,
4340 Callee.getAbstractInfo(), Attrs, CallingConv,
4341 /*AttrOnCallSite=*/true);
4342
4343 // Apply some call-site-specific attributes.
4344 // TODO: work this into building the attribute set.
4345
4346 // Apply always_inline to all calls within flatten functions.
4347 // FIXME: should this really take priority over __try, below?
4348 if (CurCodeDecl && CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<FlattenAttr>() &&
4349 !(TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoInlineAttr>())) {
4350 Attrs =
4351 Attrs.addAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
4352 llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
4353 }
4354
4355 // Disable inlining inside SEH __try blocks.
4356 if (isSEHTryScope()) {
4357 Attrs =
4358 Attrs.addAttribute(getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
4359 llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
4360 }
4361
4362 // Decide whether to use a call or an invoke.
4363 bool CannotThrow;
4364 if (currentFunctionUsesSEHTry()) {
4365 // SEH cares about asynchronous exceptions, so everything can "throw."
4366 CannotThrow = false;
4367 } else if (isCleanupPadScope() &&
4368 EHPersonality::get(*this).isMSVCXXPersonality()) {
4369 // The MSVC++ personality will implicitly terminate the program if an
4370 // exception is thrown during a cleanup outside of a try/catch.
4371 // We don't need to model anything in IR to get this behavior.
4372 CannotThrow = true;
4373 } else {
4374 // Otherwise, nounwind call sites will never throw.
4375 CannotThrow = Attrs.hasAttribute(llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
4376 llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
4377 }
4378
4379 // If we made a temporary, be sure to clean up after ourselves. Note that we
4380 // can't depend on being inside of an ExprWithCleanups, so we need to manually
4381 // pop this cleanup later on. Being eager about this is OK, since this
4382 // temporary is 'invisible' outside of the callee.
4383 if (UnusedReturnSizePtr)
4384 pushFullExprCleanup<CallLifetimeEnd>(NormalEHLifetimeMarker, SRetAlloca,
4385 UnusedReturnSizePtr);
4386
4387 llvm::BasicBlock *InvokeDest = CannotThrow ? nullptr : getInvokeDest();
4388
4389 SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> BundleList =
4390 getBundlesForFunclet(CalleePtr);
4391
4392 // Emit the actual call/invoke instruction.
4393 llvm::CallBase *CI;
4394 if (!InvokeDest) {
4395 CI = Builder.CreateCall(IRFuncTy, CalleePtr, IRCallArgs, BundleList);
4396 } else {
4397 llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("invoke.cont");
4398 CI = Builder.CreateInvoke(IRFuncTy, CalleePtr, Cont, InvokeDest, IRCallArgs,
4399 BundleList);
4400 EmitBlock(Cont);
4401 }
4402 if (callOrInvoke)
4403 *callOrInvoke = CI;
4404
4405 // Apply the attributes and calling convention.
4406 CI->setAttributes(Attrs);
4407 CI->setCallingConv(static_cast<llvm::CallingConv::ID>(CallingConv));
4408
4409 // Apply various metadata.
4410
4411 if (!CI->getType()->isVoidTy())
4412 CI->setName("call");
4413
4414 // Update largest vector width from the return type.
4415 if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(CI->getType()))
4416 LargestVectorWidth = std::max(LargestVectorWidth,
4417 VT->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
4418
4419 // Insert instrumentation or attach profile metadata at indirect call sites.
4420 // For more details, see the comment before the definition of
4421 // IPVK_IndirectCallTarget in InstrProfData.inc.
4422 if (!CI->getCalledFunction())
4423 PGO.valueProfile(Builder, llvm::IPVK_IndirectCallTarget,
4424 CI, CalleePtr);
4425
4426 // In ObjC ARC mode with no ObjC ARC exception safety, tell the ARC
4427 // optimizer it can aggressively ignore unwind edges.
4428 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
4429 AddObjCARCExceptionMetadata(CI);
4430
4431 // Suppress tail calls if requested.
4432 if (llvm::CallInst *Call = dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(CI)) {
4433 if (TargetDecl && TargetDecl->hasAttr<NotTailCalledAttr>())
4434 Call->setTailCallKind(llvm::CallInst::TCK_NoTail);
4435 }
4436
4437 // Add metadata for calls to MSAllocator functions
4438 if (getDebugInfo() && TargetDecl &&
4439 TargetDecl->hasAttr<MSAllocatorAttr>())
4440 getDebugInfo()->addHeapAllocSiteMetadata(CI, RetTy, Loc);
4441
4442 // 4. Finish the call.
4443
4444 // If the call doesn't return, finish the basic block and clear the
4445 // insertion point; this allows the rest of IRGen to discard
4446 // unreachable code.
4447 if (CI->doesNotReturn()) {
4448 if (UnusedReturnSizePtr)
4449 PopCleanupBlock();
4450
4451 // Strip away the noreturn attribute to better diagnose unreachable UB.
4452 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Unreachable)) {
4453 // Also remove from function since CallBase::hasFnAttr additionally checks
4454 // attributes of the called function.
4455 if (auto *F = CI->getCalledFunction())
4456 F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
4457 CI->removeAttribute(llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
4458 llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
4459
4460 // Avoid incompatibility with ASan which relies on the `noreturn`
4461 // attribute to insert handler calls.
4462 if (SanOpts.hasOneOf(SanitizerKind::Address |
4463 SanitizerKind::KernelAddress)) {
4464 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
4465 llvm::IRBuilder<>::InsertPointGuard IPGuard(Builder);
4466 Builder.SetInsertPoint(CI);
4467 auto *FnType = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
4468 llvm::FunctionCallee Fn =
4469 CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FnType, "__asan_handle_no_return");
4470 EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(Fn);
4471 }
4472 }
4473
4474 EmitUnreachable(Loc);
4475 Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
4476
4477 // FIXME: For now, emit a dummy basic block because expr emitters in
4478 // generally are not ready to handle emitting expressions at unreachable
4479 // points.
4480 EnsureInsertPoint();
4481
4482 // Return a reasonable RValue.
4483 return GetUndefRValue(RetTy);
4484 }
4485
4486 // Perform the swifterror writeback.
4487 if (swiftErrorTemp.isValid()) {
4488 llvm::Value *errorResult = Builder.CreateLoad(swiftErrorTemp);
4489 Builder.CreateStore(errorResult, swiftErrorArg);
4490 }
4491
4492 // Emit any call-associated writebacks immediately. Arguably this
4493 // should happen after any return-value munging.
4494 if (CallArgs.hasWritebacks())
4495 emitWritebacks(*this, CallArgs);
4496
4497 // The stack cleanup for inalloca arguments has to run out of the normal
4498 // lexical order, so deactivate it and run it manually here.
4499 CallArgs.freeArgumentMemory(*this);
4500
4501 // Extract the return value.
4502 RValue Ret = [&] {
4503 switch (RetAI.getKind()) {
4504 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand: {
4505 auto coercionType = RetAI.getCoerceAndExpandType();
4506
4507 Address addr = SRetPtr;
4508 addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(addr, coercionType);
4509
4510 assert(CI->getType() == RetAI.getUnpaddedCoerceAndExpandType());
4511 bool requiresExtract = isa<llvm::StructType>(CI->getType());
4512
4513 unsigned unpaddedIndex = 0;
4514 for (unsigned i = 0, e = coercionType->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
4515 llvm::Type *eltType = coercionType->getElementType(i);
4516 if (ABIArgInfo::isPaddingForCoerceAndExpand(eltType)) continue;
4517 Address eltAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, i);
4518 llvm::Value *elt = CI;
4519 if (requiresExtract)
4520 elt = Builder.CreateExtractValue(elt, unpaddedIndex++);
4521 else
4522 assert(unpaddedIndex == 0);
4523 Builder.CreateStore(elt, eltAddr);
4524 }
4525 // FALLTHROUGH
4526 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4527 }
4528
4529 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
4530 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect: {
4531 RValue ret = convertTempToRValue(SRetPtr, RetTy, SourceLocation());
4532 if (UnusedReturnSizePtr)
4533 PopCleanupBlock();
4534 return ret;
4535 }
4536
4537 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
4538 // If we are ignoring an argument that had a result, make sure to
4539 // construct the appropriate return value for our caller.
4540 return GetUndefRValue(RetTy);
4541
4542 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
4543 case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
4544 llvm::Type *RetIRTy = ConvertType(RetTy);
4545 if (RetAI.getCoerceToType() == RetIRTy && RetAI.getDirectOffset() == 0) {
4546 switch (getEvaluationKind(RetTy)) {
4547 case TEK_Complex: {
4548 llvm::Value *Real = Builder.CreateExtractValue(CI, 0);
4549 llvm::Value *Imag = Builder.CreateExtractValue(CI, 1);
4550 return RValue::getComplex(std::make_pair(Real, Imag));
4551 }
4552 case TEK_Aggregate: {
4553 Address DestPtr = ReturnValue.getValue();
4554 bool DestIsVolatile = ReturnValue.isVolatile();
4555
4556 if (!DestPtr.isValid()) {
4557 DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(RetTy, "agg.tmp");
4558 DestIsVolatile = false;
4559 }
4560 BuildAggStore(*this, CI, DestPtr, DestIsVolatile);
4561 return RValue::getAggregate(DestPtr);
4562 }
4563 case TEK_Scalar: {
4564 // If the argument doesn't match, perform a bitcast to coerce it. This
4565 // can happen due to trivial type mismatches.
4566 llvm::Value *V = CI;
4567 if (V->getType() != RetIRTy)
4568 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, RetIRTy);
4569 if (TargetDecl && RetTy->isPointerType()) {
4570 // By the time this is called, we've got the canonical form of the
4571 // function type, stripping typedefs. We need to rediscover them to
4572 // create the opaque form.
4573 QualType Ty = cast<ValueDecl>(TargetDecl)->getType();
4574 if (const FunctionType *FT = dyn_cast<FunctionType>(Ty)) {
4575 if (const TypedefType *TT = dyn_cast<TypedefType>(FT->getReturnType())) {
4576 // If this is a #pragma opaque return type, and we can see the
4577 // key, then we should decode it so that we can use it. DCE
4578 // should later strip away the decoding if we don't use the
4579 // result.
4580
4581 // TT->getDecl() could be a TypedefDecl or a TypedefNameDecl
4582 const TypedefDecl* TD = dyn_cast<TypedefDecl>(TT->getDecl());
4583 VarDecl *Key = TD ? TD->getOpaqueKey() : nullptr;
4584 if (Key) {
4585 llvm::Value *KeyV = CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalVar(Key);
4586 CharUnits Alignment = getContext().getDeclAlign(Key);
4587 Address Addr(V, Alignment);
4588 KeyV = Builder.CreateLoad(Addr);
4589 // If this is CHERI, enforce this in hardware
4590 if (RetTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGM.getContext())) {
4591 unsigned CapAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCHERICapabilityAS();
4592 llvm::Value *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_unseal);
4593 llvm::Type *CapPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(Int8Ty, CapAS);
4594 V = Builder.CreateCall(F,
4595 {Builder.CreateBitCast(V, CapPtrTy),
4596 Builder.CreateBitCast(KeyV, CapPtrTy)});
4597 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, RetIRTy);
4598 } else {
4599 KeyV = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(KeyV, IntPtrTy);
4600 V = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(V, IntPtrTy);
4601 V = Builder.CreateXor(V, KeyV);
4602 V = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(V, RetIRTy);
4603 }
4604 }
4605 }
4606 }
4607 }
4608 return RValue::get(V);
4609 }
4610 }
4611 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
4612 }
4613
4614 Address DestPtr = ReturnValue.getValue();
4615 bool DestIsVolatile = ReturnValue.isVolatile();
4616
4617 if (!DestPtr.isValid()) {
4618 DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(RetTy, "coerce");
4619 DestIsVolatile = false;
4620 }
4621
4622 // If the value is offset in memory, apply the offset now.
4623 Address StorePtr = emitAddressAtOffset(*this, DestPtr, RetAI);
4624 CreateCoercedStore(CI, StorePtr, DestIsVolatile, *this);
4625
4626 return convertTempToRValue(DestPtr, RetTy, SourceLocation());
4627 }
4628
4629 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
4630 llvm_unreachable("Invalid ABI kind for return argument");
4631 }
4632
4633 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled ABIArgInfo::Kind");
4634 } ();
4635
4636 // Emit the assume_aligned check on the return value.
4637 if (Ret.isScalar() && TargetDecl) {
4638 if (const auto *AA = TargetDecl->getAttr<AssumeAlignedAttr>()) {
4639 llvm::Value *OffsetValue = nullptr;
4640 if (const auto *Offset = AA->getOffset())
4641 OffsetValue = EmitScalarExpr(Offset);
4642
4643 llvm::Value *Alignment = EmitScalarExpr(AA->getAlignment());
4644 llvm::ConstantInt *AlignmentCI = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Alignment);
4645 EmitAlignmentAssumption(Ret.getScalarVal(), RetTy, Loc, AA->getLocation(),
4646 AlignmentCI->getZExtValue(), OffsetValue);
4647 } else if (const auto *AA = TargetDecl->getAttr<AllocAlignAttr>()) {
4648 llvm::Value *AlignmentVal = CallArgs[AA->getParamIndex().getLLVMIndex()]
4649 .getRValue(*this)
4650 .getScalarVal();
4651 EmitAlignmentAssumption(Ret.getScalarVal(), RetTy, Loc, AA->getLocation(),
4652 AlignmentVal);
4653 }
4654 }
4655
4656 return Ret;
4657}

4659CGCallee CGCallee::prepareConcreteCallee(CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
4660 if (isVirtual()) {
4661 const CallExpr *CE = getVirtualCallExpr();
4662 return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().getVirtualFunctionPointer(
4663 CGF, getVirtualMethodDecl(), getThisAddress(), getVirtualFunctionType(),
4664 CE ? CE->getBeginLoc() : SourceLocation());
4665 }
4666
4667 return *this;
4668}

4672Address CodeGenFunction::EmitVAArg(VAArgExpr *VE, Address &VAListAddr) {

4674 ? EmitMSVAListRef(VE->getSubExpr())
4675 : EmitVAListRef(VE->getSubExpr());
